title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter chips and butterscotch chips together.
Add peanuts and potatoes.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray nonstick spray in muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or so.
Makes 12.
Very easy and delicious.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Then mix in larger bowl the 2 boxes pudding, milk and Cool Whip; then mix all together.
Use electric mixer, then layer in clean and lined with plastic wrap flowerpot:
dirt first (Oreos), until all used.
Use Cool Whip lid in bottom of flower pot.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate overnight.
Slice thin - 1 orange and 1 lemon, place in punch for decoration and flavor.
A double batch makes 3 gallons.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger in saucepan.
Add onions and green peppers. Pour all liquids, beans, etc., into crock-pot.
Add cooked hamburger to crock-pot.
Simmer until you are ready to enjoy.

title: chicken, rice and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken in chunks and saute in oil in skillet pan.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Cook rice and broccoli according to directions.
Set aside.
Chop broccoli finely.
In a large bowl, mix chicken, celery, onion, rice and broccoli until blended.
Add both cans of soup.
Do not add water to soup.
Stir until mixed.
Pour half of mixture into a 3-quart casserole dish. Top with 1/2 of the cheese.
Add rest of mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring often. Add half and half, peppers and cheese.
Heat until warmed through.

title: maple chicken
directions: Mix syrup, oil, wine vinegar, tomato puree, sherry, soy sauce, curry powder, marjoram, garlic, salt and pepper together. Put chicken in 2-quart casserole; pour mixture over chicken. Cover; let sit for three hours at room temperature.
Then add remaining ingredients that have been chopped together.
Place in uncovered casserole and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: waffles divan
directions: Melt, stirring, cream cheese over low heat.
Stir in soup until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over waffles. (Optional:
Garnish with chopped tomato.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice lasagna
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: olive mexican fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onions in deep skillet.
Stir in beans, corn, chilies and olives.
In a 2-quart casserole, making several layers of each, sprinkle the top with cheese and arrange tortilla chips around edge.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: tossed green salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except the dressing.
Add the dressing just before serving.

title: hot dog appetizer
directions: Put all
ingredients
in a pan and simmer all day.
Use toothpicks to pick up hot dog bites.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 3 days. (To avoid discoloration, place apple slices in a large Ziploc bag and cover completely with pineapple juice.)

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients.
Place dough in covered bowl in refrigerator until ready to use.
You need not let dough rise before baking.
It is ready to use immediately as desired.
Roll or pat out on floured board and cut out as for regular biscuits.
Bake at 450° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
This dough will keep for a week or longer in refrigerator.
Yield: Each 2 cups will make about 10 or 12 biscuits.

title: corn muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: sole with butter, lemon and parsley
directions: Preheat oven to 225° in order to warm an ovenproof platter.

title: ladyfinger cheesecake
directions: Note:
Do not use crumbs that come with mix.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper; cool and store.

title: onion spread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on small pieces of rye bread.
Put under broiler for 3 minutes.

title: fried field corn
directions: Make thin cuttings from each ear of corn and scrape the rest from the cob.
Place in heavy skillet with melted butter.
Add salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook slowly on low heat, adding water as needed and stirring often.
Field corn expands as it cooks, so this will make a lot.
Cook about 40 minutes.
Add milk.
Place in 350° oven and cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tomatoes 'n rice
directions: In a large pot, cook fatback.
Remove fatback.
In same pot with fatback grease, add tomatoes, rice, water and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil; turn on low and cook for 15 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: cheese tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese over tortillas.
Top with 2 slices of cheese and 2 ham slices.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap each roll securely in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Cut each roll into 6 pieces; secure ends with toothpick.
Serve with salsa or picante sauce.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add garlic, chili powder, cumin, oregano, tomatoes and soups.
Add boned chicken.

title: squash tossed salad
directions: Break or cut lettuce in bowl.
Add all other ingredients. Toss.
Serve with or without dressing, as desired.

title: mollie's dill pickles
directions: Pack 5 (1-quart) jars with fresh cucumbers.
Add 1 head fresh dill and 1 tablespoon sugar to each jar.
Set aside.
Combine water, salt and vinegar.
Boil 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion
and
bacon bits in small saucepan.
Mix in large bowl
pork and beans, onion powder, garlic powder, salt, pepper, sugar,
catsup
and mustard.
Add onion and bacon bits and put
in baking
dish
(optional:
add
more bacon bits to top).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sarah's lemon pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, milk and salt in double boiler until thick and smooth, stirring frequently.
Add beaten egg yolks; cook a minute or 2 longer.
Add lemon juice and butter; stir and remove from heat.

title: cranberry tangerine smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients, except garnish, in a blender.
Blend for a few seconds on high speed or until ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Pour into a large glass and garnish with strawberry.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: In large salad bowl, layer ingredients, beginning with lettuce on bottom.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple, reserving juice; set fruit aside. Add enough water to juice to make 1/2 cup, set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in juice mixture.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pecans, oranges and pineapple; pour into bowl or mold.
Chill until firm.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix together; heat through.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In a large saucepan, press garlic.
Add butter, lemon juice , salt, oregano and pepper.
Add 1/2 of parsley.

title: luby's brownie piewarren, texas
directions: Beat egg whites in electric mixer until creamy.
Add sugar a little at a time until whites are very stiff.
Add pecans and cracker crumbs and mix well.

title: raisin rice
directions: Cook the rice.	While it cooks, saute onion and almonds in butter.
Add
raisins
and	heat
thoroughly.
When rice is cooked, mix everything together.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Drain. Combine rest of ingredients with macaroni. Cover and chill.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Line a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Let cream cheese and milk come to room temperature.
Beat cheese until smooth, add milk and extract.
Put remaining ingredients, except cherries and Cool Whip, in a large bowl.
Gradually add milk mixture.
Beat well until smooth and then add Cool Whip.
Pour over ladyfingers and refrigerate overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
This makes a stiff dough and I have to mix it with my hands.
Use hands to form dough into crescent shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 10 minutes or until slightly brown around edges.
Roll hot cookies in powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: lickety split peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Mix sugar, eggs, together then add peanut butter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until the bottoms brown.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Mix the sugar and cinnamon.
Separate the crescent rolls into 16 triangles.
Dip marshmallows in melted butter, then roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place on shortest side of triangle. Fold corners over marshmallow and roll toward opposite end, sealing all edges.
Dip again in melted shortening and place melted side in a muffin cup or on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from the pan immediately.
Drizzle with glaze of powdered sugar and milk while warm.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: This make about 2 dozen golf ball size balls.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Chill and serve cold.

title: stir-fry medley
directions: Chop vegetables.
Heat salad oil to medium-high.
Stir-fry vegetables 3 to 4 minutes.
Add mushrooms, water, salt and sugar. Cover; cook 5 minutes.

title: asparagus tuna casserole
directions: Line an 8 x 10-inch casserole dish with the cooked, drained noodles.
Top the noodles with the ingredients following in the order given.
Place in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: willard scott's favorite red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour batter into 3 pans.
Bake for 20 minutes.
When layers are cool, ice.

title: tasty baked beans
directions: Place pork and beans in a large pan and set aside. Mix ground chuck with onions in a skillet and cook until meat is done. Add tomato soup, sugar, molasses, mustard, and brown sugar; heat until mixture is warm. Add mixture to pork and beans and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Delicious!

title: rice and chicken pie
directions: In skillet on medium-high heat, cook chicken in butter.
Stir in seasoning mix and water; cook until thickened, about 3 minutes. Combine rice, 1/2 cup salsa, egg and 1 cup cheese.
Place in 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Top with chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese; let stand 10 minutes.
Garnish as desired.

title: country club eggs
directions: Place bread cubes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add ham or sausage; beat eggs.
Add milk and spices. Pour over ingredients in pan and drizzle with melted butter. Refrigerate overnight or longer.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until eggs are set.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and chillies.
Put all chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with half of chicken mixture, half of cheese. Repeat.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk.
Add shortening and sugar.
Add bananas.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Heat molasses and lard to melt lard.
When lard is melted, mix in soda.
Mix sugar, sour milk and egg and add.
Mix remaining ingredients well and add.
Cool overnight.
Roll out and bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
I use round cutters sometimes and also Christmas and Easter cutter designs such as rabbits, crosses, birds, stars, bells and Santa's boots.
You can sprinkle top of cookie with sugar or frost.

title: nuttie buddie pie
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and then milk. Mix together.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust.
Freeze.

title: daiquiri punch
directions: Mix corn syrup and rum in punch bowl, stirring to blend.
Stir in daiquiri mix.
Just before serving, add soda water, then carefully slide in ice ring.
Add lime slices.
Makes about 25 punch cup servings.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large plastic container and freeze.
Scoop out into glasses; pour lemon-lime soda on top. Makes a great summer drink.

title: nacho strata
directions: Combine refried beans and seasoning mixes in bowl and mix well.
Spread into 8 x 12-inch dish.
Layer dip, sour cream, black olives, tomatoes, onions and chilies over bean layer.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage, then add the vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until thick and pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: drop chocolate cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar, egg, milk, soda, flour and cocoa. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan (leave graham crackers whole) with crackers.
Mix other ingredients in bowl and pour over top of crackers. Chill for 2 hours.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juice.
Mix Tang with dry pudding and use pineapple juice to make pudding as directed.
Blend in fruit and chill.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Put rice if uncooked in double boiler with water to cover. Boil 25 minutes.
Strain. Put rice in baking dish.
Add eggs beaten with sugar, salt, milk and raisins.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan (oblong). Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be served with cheese sauce, but not necessary.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix the onion, margarine, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Spread mixture inside roll; place the ham and cheese.
Heat in oven at 300° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: crisp pizza crust(pizza hut's)
directions: Mix sugar, oil and yeast in water.
Let stand a few minutes. Add salt and 4 cups flour.
Mix well.
Raise 1/2 hour.
Add remaining flour and knead well.
Make a bread dough.
Rise 10 minutes, uncovered.
Form into balls and flatten with palm.
Rise 10 minutes.
Put into lightly oiled pans.
Press up onto sides. Brush with oil and prick with a fork (completely).
Add sauce, cheese, etc.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes dough for 3 or 4 pizzas.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Let it congeal.

title: crispy fried okra
directions: Wash okra and cut ends off. Make okra slices 1/4-inch thick. Place slices in a large bowl.

title: mint tea
directions: Combine
tea,
mint and sugar.	Pour boiling water over tea mixture.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Remove bags and mint. Discard.
Transfer to pitcher.
Add water, juice and lemonade. Stir.

title: taffy candy
directions: Pour sugar, salt, syrup and water into a deep saucepan. Stir this up and put in the good candy thermometer. Stir until dissolved and cook until it forms a hard ball or better yet, until it reaches 260°. Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly with electric mixer. Add vanilla and continue beating for about 1 minute. Then pour in the pecans and stir until the candy looks like it will hold its shape when dropped on wax paper. We use ice tea spoons (small and easier to handle) and the two of us work quickly to drop small amounts on wax paper. Store in cookie tins.

title: rave reviews cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil in a large bowl. Stir in coconut and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Best icing is cream cheese.

title: hearty winter soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain and set aside.
In large saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Add ground meat.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: peach pizza
directions: Melt the margarine and mix with flour, brown sugar and nuts. Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Let cool completely.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole dish.
In a large bowl, mix chicken, vegetables, soup and evaporated milk.
Place directly into melted margarine.
Mix Bisquick and 2/3 cup of milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: In a large pan, mix all ingredients.
Cook very slow on low heat until pears thicken or most of water is cooked down.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water to firm ball stage (244°).
Add peanuts and continue to cook, stirring constantly until mixture is light brown in color or hard crack stage (300°).
Stir in butter, soda and salt.
Pour into greased baking sheet while still foamy. Cool slightly and stretch candy to desired thinness.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: boiled custard
directions: Scald milk with sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Beat eggs well and stir the hot milk in them slowly.
Return to double boiler and cook over simmering water, stirring constantly until mixture just coats a metal spoon.
Custard will thicken somewhat on cooling.
Do not cook until thick for this will cause it to curdle. Remove immediately from heat and set pan of custard in cold water. Add vanilla and chill before serving.
Serve in sherbet glasses or use as a sauce for cake or pudding.
Also, can use as a quick "picker upper" for sick people.

title: lasagna
directions: Put enough spaghetti sauce in large baking pan to cover bottom of pan.
Layer uncooked lasagna noodles, spaghetti sauce, cheeses and dollops of cottage cheese until approximately 3-4 layers are in pan.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour 15 minutes, until fork placed through noodles goes through smoothly.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oregano, Italian seasoning, basil, garlic salt, salt, and pepper together for batter.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture and then into bread crumbs.
In a large skillet saute the eggplant in the oil until browned on both sides. Arrange in a baking dish.
In the same skillet saute the onions and mushrooms adding more oil. Layer half the mixture over the eggplant, half the tomato sauce and half cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake for 45 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sunflower seeds or almonds, and chill for 2 hours.
Add seeds just before serving.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, add jello and salt. Let cool.
Pour over fresh strawberries in shell.
Cover with whipped topping or fresh whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Partially cook bacon; add celery and onion.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add clam liquid, tomatoes, water, potatoes, carrots, green pepper, salt, thyme and Tabasco sauce.
Cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend 2 tablespoons cold water with 2 tablespoons flour.
Add some of the hot liquid until blended, then add to soup.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Add clams and heat through.

title: stained glass fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt candy coating, condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla extract and gumdrops.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store tightly covered at room temperature or in icebox.

title: chewies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread into a thin pan and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 325.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Roll out.
Cut and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: wacky wok chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in 1-inch squares. Set aside.
Slice all vegetables, preferably in a food processor. Set aside.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and eggs in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Add nuts, flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and bananas to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased bread pan and bake at 350° for approximately 60 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually and stir in flavorings.
Bake in a heavy tube pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hot mexican cider
directions: Combine apple cider and lemon juice in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat until mixture simmers.
Add tequila and orange liqueur. Cook until heated.
Pour over lemon slices.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: grandpa's chops
directions: You will need a frying pan with 2 to 3 tablespoons cooking oil and a 9 x 11-inch glass baking dish.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in greased casserole. Season each layer with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix and spread on favorite crackers.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze until ready to bake.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Set balls on ungreased baking sheet and bake until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with mustard sauce.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together in 1 bowl the drained pineapple and cheese.
In another bowl mix flour, pineapple juice and sugar.
Pour this over the pineapple and cheese mixture; toss until well coated.
Pour this into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter and crumble crackers; mix together and spread on top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: plain basic cookies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat to blend.
Drop by heaping tablespoon on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° (moderate) oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add 2 cups chocolate chips or raisins or coconut if you like.
Makes 4 dozen large cookies.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add one egg at a time.
Beat and sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add syrup and vanilla.
Mix well.
Place in large baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter round-ups
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in peanut butter.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to cream mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats. Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. With tins or forks, press to make crisscross on each.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes to 15 minutes.

title: grosmommy's oya dutch
directions: Melt
margarine in a cake pan.
Mix everything up; pour it in the pan and bake it for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: spaghetti and sauce
directions: Cover and cook slowly about 1 hour. Put 1 box spaghetti noodles on to boil. Cook until tender; drain. Put sauce over spaghetti as it is being served.

title: 7-up pie
directions: Boil 7-Up, turn off heat and dissolve jello.
Add ice cream, keep stirring until ice cream is smooth and dissolved.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and milk to make batter.
Pour into melted butter.
Add hot fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° until batter rises over fruit and browns.

title: grandma's pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple.
Add sour cream, Cool Whip and marshmallows.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 1 large cake tube pan.
Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup milk and blend.
Add eggs one at a time and blend after each addition.
Add remaining milk and flour, blend.
Add flavoring and blend well.
Put cake in cold oven; turn oven to 325° for 1 hour; turn to 350° for 1/2 hour.
Let cool in oven.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Layer noodles, peas, tuna and mushroom soup until all is used. Put cracker crumbs on top and add dots of butter and pepper.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix together and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together; preheat oven to 350°.
Use Bundt cake pan; spray with Pam and sprinkle entire pan with sugar.
Pour in batter and bake.

title: filled cheese pastry
directions: Cream butter well. Add cream cheese and blend well. Stir in flour which has been sifted. Chill. Roll out dough and cut into squares or triangles and fill with jam, cooked prunes or any other cooked fruits, drained well of juice. Fold dough and pinch together. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry soda pop cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Mix strawberry jello and chill for awhile (like syrup).
Let cake cool.
Poke holes in top.
Pour 3/4 of jello over the top, then pour 1/2 of strawberry soda.
Let it sit for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Put pudding next, then top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: original quaker oats cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: christmas fruitcake cookies
directions: Cut fruit small.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs slightly, then beat well.
Add fruit and whiskey.
Combine flour and spices; add to liquid mixture.
Drop on greased pan by teaspoon.
Bake in 300° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes a bunch!

title: black bean quesadillas
directions: In a small bowl, with fork, slightly mash black beans and stir in scallions, pepper, onion, lime juice, parsley and garlic.
Set aside.

title: creamy smothered hamburger steaks
directions: Mix hamburger, salt, pepper, onion and egg together.
In another bowl, pour the milk over the bread and Ritz crackers until softened, then add to ingredients and mix well.
Make into 8 patties and flour each patty on both sides.
Panfry with lid over low heat, turning patties often.
When steaks are done, pour a can of cream of chicken soup over all the patties and let simmer for about 3 minutes.

title: mardi gras party cake
directions: Melt chips in water and cool.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Blend in eggs, 1 at a time; beat well.
Blend in melted chips.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour into two 9-inch round pans that are well greased and floured on bottoms.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread filling in between layers and on top.
Frost sides with frosting or Cool Whip.

title: irish goulash
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain and rinse.
Add raw ground beef, onions, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer on low heat until ground beef and onion are cooked.

title: baked stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Bake the potatoes for 1 hour or until they are tender when pierced with a fork.

title: chilled fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pineapple refrigerator dessert
directions: Spread 1 cup crumbs in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Spread over other mixture in pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining crumbs. Refrigerate several hours.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Pack in an 8-inch pan; store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from pan; slice dough into 3 sections.
Slice each section into third sticks. Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let ingredients be at room temperature and mix.
If mix is very soft, refrigerate a few minutes and then form into a ball and wrap in pecans.
Refrigerate to keep.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line a large cookie sheet with foil. Spray with Pam.
Lay saltine crackers edge to edge, breaking to fit if needed.
Cover completely.
Melt butter and brown sugar over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute only!
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda to mixture.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over crackers and spread quickly to cover all crackers.
Bake for no longer than 10 minutes.
Check to be sure syrup does not caramelize.
Remove to cooling rack.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let melt 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread with tines of fork to cover toffee layer.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool or chill.
Break into small pieces.

title: macaroon pie(3 pies)
directions: Roll crackers to make crumbs.
Chop dates and mix with crumbs. Beat egg whites until very stiff, as for a meringue.
Carefully fold in remaining ingredients with wooden spoon but be sure to blend thoroughly.
Divide into three 9-inch pie tins and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Use whipped cream topping if desired.

title: ham, tomato and cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine yogurt, mustard and horseradish; blend well.
Spread yogurt mixture on cut sides of rolls.
On bottom halves of rolls, layer lettuce, ham, tomato slices and cucumber slices.
Cover with top half.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 2 quart casserole. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: markham's baked brie
directions: Smear pesto sauce in a circle roughly the same size as the Brie, on an oven-safe baking dish.
I use a quiche pan, slightly larger then the Brie round.
Place the uncut Brie round on top of the pesto sauce.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve immediately with torn pieces of French bread.
When cut open, the Brie will be runny and hot.

title: quickie rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Wash cauliflower and broccoli. Remove leaves and separate flowerets into bite size pieces. Combine all vegetables in a large bowl. Combine Miracle Whip, oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with bacon bits.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together flour and salt.
Stir ingredients together and add nuts.
Chill dough. Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet (cookies do not spread).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, or until set but not brown.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add all of the other ingredients.
Layer, beginning with sauce mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Alternate with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until bubbly.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until cheese is melted.

title: cholesterol free carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 10-inch fluted tube pan with cooking spray.
In a medium bowl beat sugar, egg substitute, oil and vanilla until smooth.

title: sweet potato boats
directions: Boil sweet potatoes with skin on.
When cooked, not mushy, drain and peel. Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out middle so they look like boats.
Fill with whole berry cranberry sauce.
Pour syrup over and bake in a 350° oven about 20
minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix about half of the cake mix, vegetable oil, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until smooth.

Stir in remaining cake mix, chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes (centers will be soft). Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: twinkies cake
directions: Cut twinkies lengthwise and layer, icing side up, in a 9 by 13 inch pan.
Mix vanilla pudding according to the box directions and spread over twinkies.
Add bananas and strawberries, spread cool whip over fruit.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn flake crisps
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in remainder of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing to cooling rack.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Mix everything together until well blended.
Pour into well greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornflake topped potatoes
directions: Mix together above ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix 2 cups crushed cornflakes to 1/4 cup melted butter and spread on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add flour, sifted with soda and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand after adding apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onions.
Separate and soak in ice water for 1 hour.
Drain and dry.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine egg and milk and add to dry mixture; beat until smooth.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: honey nut bread
directions: Mix honey, egg, milk, flour, baking powder, salt and pecans all together.
Put into greased and floured loaf pan.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake in a slow oven for about 40 minutes or 1 hour.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Mix and cook on low heat for 15 minutes. Serve over Corn Bread Dressing.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9x5x3 inch loaf pans.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl.
Beat pumpkin, oil, eggs, and water together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Pour one half of batter into each loaf pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Remove from pans after 10 minutes.

title: banghetti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add soups, water, celery and onion.
Cook until done.
Add noodles and peas.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Set in oven until cheese melts.

title: coca-cola chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour an 11 x 17 inch pan.
Sift together the dry ingredients and set aside.
In saucepan, heat butter and coca-cola until the butter melts.
Add the eggs, vanilla and buttermilk and mix well.
Add the liquid to the dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
The batter will be very thin.
Pour into the prepared pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This Cake Must Be Iced Warm!

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german potato salad(for 25)
directions: Fry bacon and remove part of drippings.
Thicken drippings with flour.
Add vinegar, sugar and water; pour over potatoes, onion and hard-boiled eggs.
Simmer together a few minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: flaky herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, basil and oregano.
Dip 1 cutlet into yogurt and then into crumb mixture, coating both sides evenly.
Repeat with other cutlet.

title: rick's chipped beef dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter.
In small baking dish, combine rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle sauteed pecans on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade ranch dressing
directions: Put milk in bowl with vinegar and let stand until curdled, then add all other ingredients.
Use whip and beat lightly until fluffy.
(Do not use beater.)

title: fresh blender applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend at medium speed until smooth, about 1 minute.
Serve at room temperature or chill. Makes 3 cups.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press 1/2 inch thick in pan. Cut into pieces.
Chill before serving.

title: peaches 'n cream cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, pudding mix, baking powder, salt, egg, milk and butter in large mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch deep dish pie plate.
Drain peaches well, reserving liquid.
Arrange peach slices atop the batter.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach juice in medium bowl.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed 2 to 3 minutes.
Carefully spread atop peaches to within 1-inch of edge of pie plate.
Stir 1 tablespoon sugar with 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon; sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lipton california mashed potatoes
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are very tender. Drain; return potatoes to saucepan.
Mash potatoes.
Stir in parsley and onion recipe soup mix, blended with hot milk and sour cream.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: lunchbox cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, powdered sugar, margarine and shortening; beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; blend well.
Spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flours, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Blend at low speed until well mixed.
Stir in peanuts and almond chips.
Shape heaping tablespoons into balls (using dough).
Roll in sugar.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Bake at 350°. Wash beans. Add boiling water. Cover and let stand 1 hour or longer. Cook beans in same water until tender (about 1 hour). Add seasonings. Pour into 2 baking pans. Place salt pork on top of beans. Bake until top is brown (about 1 hour).

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain well.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir well.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (high 3 hours).
Serves 10.
May be frozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir spinach, sour cream, mayo, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions until well mixed.
Cover and chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir well.
If desired, spoon into round bread bowl.
Hawaiian bread is good.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken. Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk. Coat heavily with flour. Arrange chicken breast side down in dish. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Turn chicken and bake 10 minutes. Stir remaining buttermilk and can of soup. Pour mixture over chicken and bake 10 minutes more (cover with foil to prevent excessive browning). Serve over hot rice.

title: strawberry tea punch
directions: Pour water over bags; boil four minutes.
Remove tea bags and stir in sugar, lemonade and strawberries.
Serve over ice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat. Cook for 20 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Cool to room temperature; refrigerate (cover tightly).
Will keep up to 2 weeks in fridge.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix 3 cans of water to each can tomato paste.
First put a little olive oil in a large pan.
Then add a little chopped garlic and onion.
Fry this and then add the tomato paste.
Mix with water.
Let this come to a boil.
Add baking soda and then the other ingredients.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, soda and eggs until smooth.
Add flour and bananas; stir until smooth.
Add nuts; stir.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve open-face over grilled hamburger buns.

title: herbed peas
directions: Add seasonings to peas.
If you want variations, add chopped onion and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Cook until tender and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add all ingredients to the browned hamburger; simmer a couple of hours until cooked down and thickened.
Remove the bay leaf. Serve over spaghetti style pasta.
Makes 10 to 12 large servings.

title: broccoli(quick, easy, delicious)
directions: Clean broccoli and cook with 1 teaspoon salt and butter.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chicken, cream of mushroom soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 3 or 4 minutes.

title: peach raisin-bran snack cake
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar and Raisin Bran and set aside. Combine flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
Beat oleo, sugar and eggs until well blended; stir in peaches.
Add flour mixture.
Add cereal mixture.
Stir well.

title: ruth's banana cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in separate bowl.
Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs and buttermilk.
Cream in bananas next with creamy mixture.
Add in dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: thai turkey rice soup
directions: Place turkey in medium sized pot.
Add 3 cups of water. Bring to boil.
Add cooked rice, onion, fish sauce and pepper. Cook for 10 minutes.
Put in serving bowl (or small soup bowl). Top with green vegetables. Serve hot.
Makes two to three servings.

title: brownies (coombs)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Dissolve chocolate in boiling water.
Add salt, flour, vanilla and nuts. Spread thin in two pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Crush Doritos and line bottom of one large pan or 2 9 x 13 pans.
Add hamburger, onions, cheese, tomatoes, lettuce, taco sauce, cheese and beans in order listed.
Bake at 350° on bottom rack until hot, usually 15-20 minutes.
As you serve, you may want to top with sour cream or more taco sauce.

title: salmon salad
directions: Drain salmon and flake with a fork.
Add cabbage, celery and olives; stir gently and fold in mayonnaise.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: cottage cheese potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, drain and cool.
Peel and slice. Place 4 sliced potatoes in bowl.
Cover with 1/3 of onion, 1/3 cottage cheese, 3 heaping tablespoons mayonnaise and a little pepper.
Repeat 2 more times to make 3 layers.
Sprinkle cayenne pepper on top.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours or more.
Toss and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread the crushed pineapple with juice in the pan.
Add the cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix.
Sprinkle the chopped pecans.
Cut the margarine into little squares.
Completely cover top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, until brown.
Serve with or without whipped cream.
This is better not refrigerated.

title: white chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water and cool.
Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well. Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture. Beat well until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes a three layer cake.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine peas and water. Boil 2 minutes. Rest from heat 1 hour. Add all but potatoes and carrots. Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add potatoes and carrots. Cook 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain off fat.
Separate crescent rolls and put on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Place points to center and press over bottom and sides to form a crust.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Swiss and Cheddar cheeses.
In bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: esther's devil's food cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Stir cocoa into boiling water together.
Mix soda and buttermilk together.
Add cocoa mixture to creamed mixture alternately with flour and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and oatmeal. Dissolve soda in the hot water.
Pour over mixture. Add vanilla and flour.
Roll in small balls on cookie sheet.
Pat out with your hands very thin and then press with fork.
Bake in a quick oven.

title: baked squirrel
directions: Section squirrel and flour.
Brown in skillet.
Place in covered baking dish.
Cover squirrel with ingredients.
Bake until tender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Brown sausage. Drain off excess fat.
Spread over bread.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on sausage.
Mix together half and half, milk, eggs, salt and dash of pepper.
Beat well.
Pour over layers of cheese, sausage and bread.
Let set in the refrigerator overnight.
Set out 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo.
Cook, stirring, 1 minute after mix comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: mexican pork kabobs
directions: Slice pork loin across grain into 1/4-inch slices (this is best done if meat is partially frozen).
Cut each slice lengthwise in half.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together into a stiff dough.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar or red or green sugar crystals.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber-chive dip
directions: Seed and shred cucumber.
In bowl, combine cream cheese, chives, basil and cucumber.
Garnish with chive stems and serve with assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix with other ingredients. Stir well.
Cook in pan with tight lid until cabbage is tender. This can also be baked for 2 hours in 350° oven.

title: spicy beef casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain. Stir in tomatoes, sauce, chilies, bouillon and mushrooms.
Simmer until all bouillon is dissolved.

title: rock fish pie
directions: Salt
and pepper fish.	Place
in
oblong
baking
pan. Sift flour, diced onion, pats of butter	and
a pinch of sugar over fish.
Add water, place over medium
flame	for
10 to 15 minutes. Cook potatoes until tender;
add
to
other ingredients.
Cover with favorite short crust.	Cut in strips.	Place in 450° oven until golden brown.
Serves four.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until just tender.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brenda's special salad
directions: Wash and pat dry lettuce and place on serving tray.
Place sliced tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese on lettuce in alternating pattern.
Grind garlic, fresh parsley and fennel.
Sprinkle over salad.
Sprinkle chopped olives and oil and vinegar to suit taste.

title: mandelbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and nuts.
Spray cookie sheets with Pam.
Make 2 strips and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Mixture will be very thick.

title: zucchini mock apple pie
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water about 2 minutes.
Drain well and let cool.
Mix sugars, cinnamon, tartar, corn starch and salt together.

title: dip away diet dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese.
Add onion.
Add seasoned salt.
Beat with electric beater.
When chilled, stir in pimiento.
Serve with relish sticks.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs and milk slowly. Add vanilla and coconut last.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and it's juice with the pudding mix; mix well. Add marshmallows, then nuts, then Cool Whip. Put in a dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Mix soup, milk and sour cream together and stir well.
Line bottom of dish with enough beef to cover well.
Wrap chicken with bacon and lay on top of beef.
Sprinkle with pepper and do not add salt.
Pour liquid over chicken.
Place in oven at 300° for 3 hours (time is correct).
Should dish brown too rapidly, cover with foil to finish cooking.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and margarine for 7 1/2 minutes (after starting to boil).	Remove	from
heat
and
add the chocolate chips.
Stir
until
smooth.
Add marshmallow topping, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberries.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: cucumber cream salad
directions: Blend dip, juice and sugar.
Add cucumbers and toss well. Chill.
Garnish with dill.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O together in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually stir into pie filling.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Fold sugar into sour cream just until blended.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Chill until serving time.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with thin strips of lemon peel.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, mixing well after each one.
Mix baking powder with the flour and gradually add this alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture.
Add flavoring last.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Place into cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Do not open oven for the first hour.

title: chow mein noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Save 1/2 cup noodles for top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: In skillet, heat 1/2 oil to 400°.
In bowl with fork, stir oil and all ingredients until blended.
Drop batter into hot oil.
Fry 4 minutes until browned, turning once.
With slotted spoon, remove to paper towels.
Drain.
Serve with syrup or powdered sugar.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onions in oil. Add ground beef and continue stirring until brown. Add seasoning and then all other ingredients.
After mixture begins cooking, simmer for 2 hours. Stir often. Serve with Doritos, grated cheese and sour cream.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Mix 2 heaping teaspoonfuls with 1 cup hot water.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries in blender.
Add sugar.
Chill for 2 hours. Add marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Whip cream and fold into the berry mixture.
Spoon into bowl.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze.
Serve.

title: sugar-crusted rhubarb squares
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, salt and brown sugar in bowl. Combine oil, egg, sour milk and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients, blending well. Stir in rhubarb and nuts. Spread batter in greased 9-inch square baking pan. Combine sugar, butter and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter. Bake in preheated 325° oven 55 minutes or until done. Cut in squares and serve warm or cold. Makes 9 servings.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add sugar and orange rind.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight.
Add gelatin and boiling water to cranberry mixture.
Add pecans and diced apple.
Diced celery may also be added, if desired.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: jello froth
directions: Pour jello into casserole or baking dish.
Add boiling water. Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add soft drink.
Stir.
Add ice cubes.
Stir until mixture congeals.
Take out ice cubes.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, coconut and cocoa in a large bowl; set aside. Boil in a saucepan sugar, butter and milk for 1 minute.
Mix together.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: diet muffins
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cherry-aloha nut squares
directions: Spread dry cake mix over fruit which has been spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with walnuts.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer salad as listed in tall salad bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: double decker marbled fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Place 1 cup chocolate chips in large heatproof bowl.
In 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, butter, corn syrup and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full rolling boil; boil and stir 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme; stir until smooth.
Pour one-half of peanut butter mixture over chocolate chips; stir until smooth.
Pour chocolate mixture into prepared pan; top with remaining peanut butter mixture.
Immediately sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chips over surface.
With knife or metal spatula, gently swirl chips for marbled effect.
Cool; cut into squares.
If a firmer fudge is desired, store covered in refrigerator.
Makes about 8 dozen pieces or 4 pounds candy.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and add other ingredients.
Layer cake pan with uncooked lasagna noodles, then hamburger mixture, noodles, rest of hamburger and top with noodles.
Pour 2 1/2 cups water and 2 1/2 cups salsa over top.
Cover tightly.
Cook about 1 hour at 350°. Remove.
Add 2 cups sour cream and a can of sliced olives.
Top with grated Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Put back in oven, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: dreamy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl and chill. Garnish with chopped pecans, if desired.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring broccoli, celery, onion and broth to a boil; cover and simmer 8 minutes.

title: butter glaze soup
directions: Mix noodles, broth and turkey. Start cooking this mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Grease casserole.
Place a layer of potatoes, then layer of cheese.
Alternate, ending with cheese.
Can top with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a slow cooker until potatoes are done.
Homemade cornbread and a bowl of soup are a good meal on a cold day.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: jambalaya
directions: In 3-quart pan, saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine and garlic salt until tender.
Add chicken and sausage. Cook until done, approximately 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and water to fill pan.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Season to taste.
Remove from heat.
Add rice.
Serve with salsa or plain.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in large bowl.
Add pickling salt and mix well.
Add enough water to cover.
Stir well.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain water and rinse once in cold water.
Drain and put in plastic cups or jars; add peppers and onions.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Do not heat. Pour over cucumbers.
Place lids on containers and shake.
Freeze. Keeps up to a year.

title: peach preserves
directions: Peel and pit
peaches.	Thinly	slice
(about
4 cups). Combine peaches, lemon juice
and
pectin in a large saucepan. Stir in sugar and bring
to
a
rolling boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove
from heat and skim foam. Pour hot into hot
jars,
leaving 1/4 inch	headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process for 10
minutes
in boiling water bath.
Yields about 6 (12 ounce) jars.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and spinach according to package directions. Drain both.
Add salt.
Place 1/2 of noodles in 12 x 12-inch bake dish.
Add 1/2 of spinach, cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat this one more time, starting with noodles.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Very low fat.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and softened cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring until just blended.
Stir in coconut and flavorings.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until done.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: baked sauerkraut mushroom
directions: Brown onion and dried sliced mushrooms in butter.
Add all ingredients, including water from mushrooms.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish at 325° for 1 hour.
Add more brown sugar for a sweeter taste or more water for moisture.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix in jar; keep refrigerated.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix filling and let set while making crust.
Roll enough graham crackers to make 2 cups or use package crumbs.
Mix with 1/2 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press into the bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan to form a crust or you can make 2 pies by using regular pie pans.
Cream until smooth the softened cream cheese and blend eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into crust and bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Chill pie completely before adding the topping.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 1/2 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. In saucepan, bring water and margarine to a boil.
Stir in flour until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat. By hand, beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Spread evenly on pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Simmer in crock pot on low.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl stir together real mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add celery, green pepper or red onion; toss.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Open rolls flat on cookie sheet.
Press seams together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cream softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry dressing mix together.
Spread over cooled crust. Sprinkle finely chopped vegetables over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and refrigerate an hour (more) before serving.

title: karen's apple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over the oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes. Cream butter or margarine until fluffy.
Add brown sugar and granulated sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla, eggs and oatmeal mixture.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, over low heat, melt 1 cup chips with margarine; remove from heat.
Add biscuit mix, sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chips.
Turn into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from the sides of the pan.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Cut into squares or bars.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: coconut fudge pie(microwave)
directions: Microwave butter and chocolate in a 2-quart glass bowl on High for 1 minute.
Mix in pecans, coconut and sugar.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Microwave at Medium for 8 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn at 2 minute intervals.
Stir once at 4 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown chuck in margarine; add salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cook on low heat at least 30 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain well.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and onions. Layer noodles, meat mixture and cream cheese-onion mixture. Repeat.
Sprinkle top with grated sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes, keeping covered until heated thoroughly. Remove lid and cook 10 minutes more.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Melt shortening and let cool for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Press the top of each ball with fork. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 300° until lightly brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together sugar, salt and eggs in a blender.
Add flour and spices.
Drain cooked pumpkin and add to this mixture along with the milk.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then 350° for 20 minutes.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
In a bowl, mix sifted ingredients with the sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients. Put into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate creme pie
directions: Melt stick of butter in bowl in microwave.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and cocoa to melted butter.
Stir real good! (Get lumps out!) Add small amounts of milk, stirring well to keep from being too lumpy until all milk is stirred in.
Cook on High in microwave 3 to 4 minutes, then stir well.
Repeat cooking 2 to 4 minutes at a time until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Add meringue, then brown.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix grated cheese, sugar, salt and pepper with enough mayonnaise for a spread.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook wild rice according to label instructions (55 to 60 minutes); set aside.

title: violet lemonade
directions: Soak clean purple violet petals in lemon juice for several hours.
The juice will turn a vivid pink.
Remove petals and water and sugar to taste.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: In blender, blend strawberries and lemonade concentrate.
Pour into a large punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: banana pudding(for diabetics)
directions: Mix pudding as directed using only 3 cups 2% milk.
Mix in sour cream, then Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9-inch dish, layer vanilla wafers, then bananas and pour half of the pudding mixture over this.
Repeat layers.
Top with a few vanilla wafers.

title: cheesecake(10-inch pan)
directions: Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 15 minutes. Pour mixer over crust and bake for 30 minutes on 350° or until edge starts to come away from pan.
Center will be jiggly.
Let stand to firm up.

title: special chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and cocoa.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add vinegar to milk and add to the creamed mixture alternately with the dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and hot water.
Makes two (9-inch) layers or 1 large sheet cake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Place foil baking liners into 18 to 24 muffin cups and put 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each liner.
Whip the cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and eggs (added one at a time), blending.
Fill each 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, cocoa powder, nuts or coconut and chocolate chips together; set aside.
In medium size pot, bring milk, margarine and sugar to a full boil.
When sugar dissolves, stir in dry ingredients quickly and drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Chill. Keep in refrigerator.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle Jell-O over cheese.
Fold it together.
Drain pineapple.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip and fold it in.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook slowly until soft ball stage. Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla; beat until stiff.

title: chicken broccoli fettuccine
directions: Boil chicken.
Clean off bones and cut into chunks.
In skillet or wok, cook garlic in margarine for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix soup, half and half and 1/2 cup chicken broth. Add broccoli flowerets.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over fettuccine.
Garnish with parsley and cherry tomatoes.
Sprinkle more fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: beef stew
directions: I cook this in
slow cooker.
Put all ingredients in and cook until meat and potatoes are done.
After the celery is cooked for a while, I remove it.
This is very good on a cold day or anytime.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat well in large skillet.
Drain.
Add chopped pepper and onion.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Brown a few minutes more; add chili powder and cumin.

title: turtles
directions: Melt 1 to 2 minutes on High the bark in the microwave.
Using a plastic spoon, place a small amount on wax paper, about the size of a quarter.
Place pecan halves on bark and let cool.
Melt the caramels and milk for 1 minute on High.
Place small amount on top of nuts.
Repeat step 1 and let cool.

title: armenia baker's bread
directions: Melt shortening in water.
Mix in yeast.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Knead until smooth on floured board.
Cover and let rise until double.
Make into loaves.
Place in loaf pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put asparagus in bottom of dish; mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over asparagus.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan using medium heat. Bring to boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
On wax paper, drop by spoonfuls.
Let cool.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store at room temperature in covered container. Mix 3 or 4 rounded tablespoonfuls per cup of water.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew chicken; debone and cut in bite size pieces. In greased casserole, cover bottom with crumbled Doritos. Put chicken on top of chips and cover with soup mixture. Top with crushed Doritos and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: honey nut granola
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except raisins.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake; stirring occasionally.
Stir in raisins; spread out to cool.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Bake at 325° for 20-25 minutes.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 1 qt. baking dish. In a medium bowl, mix together artichoke hearts, spinach, mayonnaise, parmesan cheese and 2 c. Monterey Jack or Mozzarella cheese.

title: dutch pound cake
directions: With a wire whip, cream butter and shortening until fluffy, then add 1/2 the sugar and cream together on medium speed of mixer.
Add the salt, baking powder and lemon extract and mix well, then stir in the rest of the sugar and beat well on medium. Gradually add eggs, 2 at a time, blending well after each addition.
Add the flour and gently mix until well blended.
Pour in milk and mix at slow speed until incorporated (approximately 1 minute).

title: beef, noodle and corn casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Saute onions and add to beef.
Cook noodles according to package.
Layer noodles, beef-onion mixture and corn; top with tomato soup.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Pat dry grated cucumber; add to cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients to cream cheese.
Mix well, using a potato masher.
Cut frozen bread into desired shapes.
Spread cream cheese mixture over bread and top with a slice of green olive.
Serve.

title: easy cinnamon graham cookies
directions: Bring margarine and brown sugar to a boil.
Add pecans to mixture.
Place crackers on cookie sheet; spread mixture over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Break into pieces and store in container.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Put in bowl in the order given.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Frost and enjoy.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil together sugar, water, shortening, salt, raisins and spices for 5 minutes.
When cool, add flour and soda dissolved in a tablespoon hot water.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 loaves.
(Loaf pan approximately 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inches.)

title: brown candy
directions: Cook together until soft ball stage.
Beat and add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Place in buttered pan.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients in a pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer; add carrots.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Serve chilled as a side dish.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Add milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins. Take 1/2 cup carrots and raisin mixture; blend with yogurt and juices. Add rest of carrots and raisins; mix well. Chill. Serve cold. Serves 6.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Mix.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix. Batter will be stiff.
Use an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: kelvin's meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, chopped green pepper and onion and crushed crackers.
Add seasoning and mix once more.
Make into a mound about 4 x 8 x 1 to 2-inches thick.
Cover with ketchup and bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice in water as usual.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Melt cheese and soup together; mix with rice and broccoli.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tropical fruit pops
directions: Combine banana, pineapple, strawberries, yogurt and honey in a blender or food processor.
Whirl until smooth.
Fill 5 ounce paper drinking cups with mixture.
Place a wooden stick in each and freeze.

title: easy potato souffle
directions: Whip all ingredients, except onion rings, together.
Put in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Add onion rings to top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Can be mixed ahead and frozen.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts with mixer.
After thoroughly mixed, add the nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Rinse rice and place in skillet or 2-quart saucepan.
Add water,
tomato puree and salt; allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Add cut vegetables, tomato sauce and bacon. Place on low heat and cook 30 to 35 minutes.
When half done, lift lid and stir, then cover and finish cooking.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain orange sections, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to measure 1 cup liquid.
In a saucepan bring syrup-water mixture to boiling.
Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in orange juice.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into eggs; return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and cream cheese; beat with a rotary beater until smooth.
Chill until partially set (the consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Fold in orange sections, sliced banana and nuts.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce lined salad plate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake in layers.
When cool, slice layers into two.

title: fruit cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package and mix all the ingredients in large pan.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese until soft.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter. Blend in milk thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Freeze and let thaw for 5 minutes before serving.

title: standard cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually, as well as well-beaten egg, milk, and flavoring.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Chill and roll to 1/4 inch.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 15 mins.
Remove from sheet as soon as taken from oven.

title: cheddar puffs
directions: Cream butter with cheese until smooth.
Blend in flour and salt; knead until it forms a soft dough.
Roll 1 teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen puffs.
Bake at 400° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze.
About 1 hour before serving, remove from freezer and refrigerate.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage. Drain well.
Put all the ingredients in a crock-pot.
Continue to stir until cheese has melted.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: In top of double boiler or in microwave, melt caramels and 1/3 cup canned milk and set aside.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel
and cut eggplant into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Dip each slice
in
egg,
then
bread crumbs.
In a large skillet, heat oil and
cook
eggplant 2 to 3 minutes on each side until tender
and browned.
Drain
on
paper	towel.	Spread	small amount of
sauce over
bottom
of
rectangular
pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Arrange half
of the eggplant slices in pan.
Cover with half
of
the sauce
and	cheeses.
Repeat
layers
with remaining eggplant, sauce and cheeses.	Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Remove cover and bake an additional 5 minutes to brown cheese.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix soda and buttermilk. Blend in egg mixture.
Add flour slowly.
Cook raisins and add to mixture along with other ingredients.
Spray 3 round cake pans with cooking spray (I prefer Baker's Joy cooking spray).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients up and put in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: healthy jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, pepper, celery and garlic in margarine in a 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat until softened.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, tomato paste and seasonings; simmer for 10 minutes. Add rice; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add ham, chicken and shrimp.
Continue cooking, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes, or until rice absorbs liquid.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: bunny's cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients; chill, then roll in finely chopped walnuts.

title: grand lagoon stuffed flounder
directions: Crab Meat Stuffing:
Combine first 7 ingredients, beginning with finely chopped bell pepper in a large bowl.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients; stir into crab meat mixture.
Stuff flounder. Leftover stuffing may be used to stuff jumbo shrimp and bake as directed for flounder or it may be shaped into croquettes and browned in hot oil.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: *Can also put in cupcake pan for snacks.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix
all ingredients except popcorn in large pan.
Boil to hard
ball	stage.	Pour
popcorn
into syrup mixture. Stir over low heat until all popcorn is coated.

title: cocktail kielbasa
directions: Place kielbasa in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix other ingredients together and pour over kielbasa. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°. (May serve with toothpicks.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over medium heat until soft ball forms.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan; cool and cut into pieces.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in slow cooker.
Set on #5 for about 2 hours, then on #2 for serving.
Offer cinnamon sticks for stirring sticks.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix all fruits together in medium to large bowl.
Add rice and Cool Whip and blend well.
Chill for 2 hours.
Serve before, during or after meals.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like pie crust. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Whip together cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip. Spread onto cooled crust. Beat pudding and milk until thick. Spread over cream cheese layer. Let set few minutes. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle more chopped nuts and shaved Hershey bar on top. Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add bacon to skillet and reduce heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Add all ingredients and blend together with beans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Heat pineapple and dry jello.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.
Keeps well in airtight container.
For smaller amount, use 1/2 ingredients.

title: oreo cookie delite
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Blend in Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Crush Oreo cookies in food chopper.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan or large dessert dish, place a layer of pudding mix and layer of cookie mix;
continue until container is full.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, approximately 30 minutes.

title: mrs. helen's mountain dew cake
directions: Pour in 3 greased layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil in large skillet until browned. Add vegetables; stir-fry until crisp-tender.

title: spinach pinwheels
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Spread mixture thinly on tortillas.
Roll tortillas.
Chill, covered, until firm.
Cut rolls into 1/2-inch slices.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil brown sugar, syrup, oleo and cream of tartar together for 5 minutes and quickly stir in baking soda.
Mix peanuts and popcorn.
Pour syrup mixture over them.
Mix thoroughly and spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Put in 200° oven for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: devilish potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, prepare au gratin potatoes according to package directions, eliminating butter or margarine.
Stir in deviled ham.
Bake according to package directions.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meat leftover pie
directions: Cover with pie crust and bake at 370° for 1 hour.
Garlic salt can be added to the pie crust.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix together sausage, cheese and Bisquick.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into small balls and bake 5 to 10 minutes at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Serve hot.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, shortening and molasses.
Add soda to sour milk and add to creamed mixture.
Add enough flour to roll nice, but do not roll too thin.
Cut into favorite shapes with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° to 400°.

title: pineapple upside cake
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over melted oleo.
Place pineapple slices or crushed pineapple drained over brown sugar.
Add cherries to pine apples as desired.

title: aunt mabel's cumberland city tennessee dumplings
