directions: Mix to form soft dough. Roll dough out very thin (1/8-inch) on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 2 x 3-inch rectangles and sprinkle lightly with flour.
Drop dumplings into boiling broth. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring often, until dumplings sink (about 5 minutes).
Serve with chicken and vegetables.
(I prefer to prepare mine before cooking when I add the salt to the flour mixture.)

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in the top of a double boiler. Stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Place cottage cheese in a food processor and process until smooth.
Add the yogurt, honey, lemon juice and strawberries and process until pureed.
Pour into prepared pie crust and chill for several hours before serving.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: On a sheet of wax paper, sprinkle together parsley flakes, chili powder, and half the pecans.
Set aside.

In a mixing bowl, mix cream cheese, garlic cheese log and grated Velveeta together. Add the other half of the pecans and 1-2 tsp. of minced garlic. Using clean hands or a mixer, thoroughly mix and blend the three cheeses, pecans and garlic together.
(Note:
Allowing cheese to soften at room temperature makes the blending process easier.) Shape cheese into a ball.
Roll cheese ball in parsley flakes, chili powder and pecans making sure cheese ball is completely coated.
Chill cheese ball overnight.
Serve with Sociable brand crackers.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice 4 or 5 medium size sweet potatoes.
Add salt and boil until almost tender.
Drain and put in baking dish.
Add at least 1/2 cube oleo, brown sugar, orange juice, crushed pineapple and nuts meats.
Bake in 400° oven until syrup thickens.
Before removing from oven, cover with marshmallows and brown.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the egg and mix well.
Add the flour and cream.
Dust a board with flour and roll the dough very thin.
Cut cookies with a water glass or round cookie cutters.
Place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for about 5 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Slice avocados in half and remove pit.
Scoop out pulp and place into bowl; mash well.
Add salsa and tomatoes well.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Serve with chips.

title: holiday spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti in salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse well in cold water.
Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine. Add ground beef and lightly brown.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushrooms and cut up tomatoes.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Add sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in a casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well if not topped with cheese.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix salt, pepper, vinegar and water. Stir together and refrigerate.
Tightly cover overnight.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: bacon dip
directions: Crush bacon bits and onion bits in wax paper.
Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate a little while before serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cooked cornbread and divide in half.
Layer 1/2 of cornbread in a 2 qt. dish.
In a bowl mix bacon, bell pepper, tomatoes, onions, and salad cubes together.
Put 1/2 of mixture over cornbread.
Put remaining cornbread on top and then a add remaining mixture.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice together and pour over the top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and serve.

title: pudding delight
directions: Cut margarine into flour as for pie crust.
Add pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip together.
Spread over top of crust.
Beat together pudding mixes and milk until it begins to thicken.
Spread over top of cheese mixture.
Spread the rest of the Cool Whip on top of pudding and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
(Best if refrigerated overnight.)
May sprinkle chopped pecans on top of Cool Whip, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as you would a cake recipe.
Line pan with wax paper. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and bell peppers. Mix mayonnaise, milk, salt, pepper, onion and vinegar. Toss with chicken mixture; chill. At serving time, add grapes and nuts; mix lightly. Poppy seed adds a nice flavor and looks pretty on top.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in margarine until onions are transparent.
Mix other ingredients with onions.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Brown in oven at 300°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into small pieces. Mix together soup, Ro-Tel, bell pepper, onion, garlic, chili powder and 1/2 cup cheese. Spray a large Pyrex pan with Pam. Line bottom with 1/2 cup crushed Doritos. Place chicken pieces on top. Pour in mixed ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour in remaining Doritos and cheese over top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: sister shepard's fried rice
directions: Stir-fry vegetables in oil.
Add meat and fry until hot. Spoon in cooked rice.
Stir gently until vegetables and meat are mixed in.
Season with soy sauce and a dash of Accent.
Cook over low heat stirring frequently until rice is warm.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Reserve.
Saute chopped or sliced onions.
Slice zucchini and lay on top of the onions; cover and steam until crisp.
Pour catsup over top of the vegetables. Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and serve hot.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir together first four ingredients; spread evenly in shallow pan.

Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle 2/3 of the nuts mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine egg whites, sugar, berries (juice and all) and lemon juice in large bowl with electric mixer.
Beat at high speed to stiff peaks, about 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over nut mixture; top with remaining nut mixture.
Freeze at least 6 hours. Cut in squares.
This recipe can also be made with fresh strawberries (2 cups sliced), increase sugar to 1 cup.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples; toss with a few drops of lemon juice. Combine with raisins, sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Turn into a 9-inch pie shell.
Dot with butter and top with second crust. Slit several times.
Bake at 400° for one hour.
Cool and ice with vanilla icing.

title: easy easy fudge cake
directions: Blend the chocolate pudding with the milk and bring to a boil. You can do this on top of the stove or in the microwave.
Stir several times to keep mixture smooth.
Stir the cake mix into the hot pudding and beat until just smooth.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking pan and sprinkle the semi-sweet bits over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until center is set.
Do not overcook.
Cake will be very moist.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put in buttered dish 1/2 of broccoli, then 1/2 cheese, then other 1/2 broccoli and then rest of cheese.
Add crackers to butter.
Put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown on top.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.

title: butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch round pans.
In a large bowl, mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until fluffy (about 3 minutes).
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour into pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool on racks.
Frost with Cocoa Fudge Frosting.

title: smoked pork chops with sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook onions in butter until tender. In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, lightly toss onion, cabbage, flour, sugar and caraway seed.
Pour vinegar over mixture.
Top with chops.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 3/4 hours or until cabbage and meat are fork-tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Combine in separate bowl the onion, soup and mayonnaise.
Add eggs.
Mix and place in casserole.
Add broccoli.
Mix oleo (butter) and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, milk, sour cream, cheese and 2 tablespoons of the melted margarine; stir gently until well combined.
Spread evenly into prepared baking dish.
In small bowl, combine crushed cornflakes with remaining 2 tablespoons margarine; sprinkle evenly over potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, until bubbling and lightly browned, about 50 minutes.

title: butter pecan fluff
directions: Prepare the butter pecan pudding.
Add Cool Whip and half of the Pecan Sandies cookies broken into small pieces.
Mix and add the rest of the crumbled cookies on top.

title: pear conserve
directions: Peel and grind
pears
or
cut
fine.
Cut up cherries; add pineapple.
Measure pulp.
Add sugar.
Cook over slow fire until thick.
Put
in sterilized glasses and cover with paraffin or seal in canning jars.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients,
adding nuts last.
Pour into standard pie shell.
Place
in
hot
oven
(450°) for about 10 minutes, then reduce heat to
and
bake until firm, about 50 minutes. After about
minutes insert silver knife blade into filling. The pie is done when knife comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: sausage bisquick
directions: Melt chopped cheese and sausage in double boiler until all ingredients blend.
Add Bisquick and mix.
Form into balls (walnut size).
Refrigerate or freeze overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
These are especially good for appetizers or parties.

title: apple carrot salad
directions: Wash apples and dice.
Put in lemon juice to prevent color change.
Combine apples, carrots and pecans or walnuts; mix with sugar and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until ready.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Make crust and pat; into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 350° for 10 minutes. Watch so it don't burn.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix.
Add yeast mixture to buttermilk and then add to dry mixture.
Knead dough enough to hold together and roll dough to 1/2 to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and fold as for pocketbook rolls.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
May be frozen.
Makes about 5 dozen rolls.

title: gourmet dog biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (except yeast) in a large bowl. Dissolve yeast in warm water or chicken stock, then mix in peanut butter.
Combine this mixture with dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: whoopie pies(cookies)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add, alternately, dry ingredients and hot water which has been added to cocoa and sour milk.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°; cool.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix together all other ingredients except crabmeat.
Add cream cheese; mix well. Add crabmeat; mix gently.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend. Add milk and salt. Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly. Add potatoes and pimento.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake in 13 x 9-inch dish for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: japanese rice
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onions, peppers and carrots. Saute until brown.
Add soy sauce and chopped meat.
Brown well. Add rice and cook until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until well blended.
Roll into dime size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 to 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Oven temperatures and cooking times may vary.)

title: festive fudge
directions: In heavy sauce pan over low heat, melt chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly onto wax paper or greased foil-lined 8 or 9 inch square pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board. Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: quick veggie salad
directions: Combine all and mix let set 2 hours.
Stir and serve.
Serves 6-8.

title: baked corn and tomatoes
directions: Mix corn and tomatoes with seasonings and pour into greased baking dish.
Spread with crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 5.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Prepare tomatoes.
Put into blender through a strainer.
Cook in enamel or stainless.
Cook down a bit.
Finely chop garlic, onions and peppers.
Put in oil.
Stir to bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes, then add to tomato juice.
Also add the spice, sugar and paste.
Cook 1 hour or more.
Stir often.
Can in sterilized jars.
Place salt in jars before you fill them.
Seal at once.
Store in a dark place.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Make in three rolls and put in refrigerator overnight.
Then slice and bake at 375°.

title: lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 16 x 11 x 2 1/2-inch pan (or a 13 x 9 x 3 to 3 1/2-inch works too).
Brown meat; stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, dry spaghetti sauce mix, V-8 juice and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes (this should be done in a large pot on stove top).

title: summer salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, mustard and vinegar in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Set aside and cool. Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Add pimentos, celery and onions.
Add the dressing and stir.
Add the grated cabbage and stir thoroughly.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Beat cake mix, sour cream, eggs, vanilla, sugar, Crisco and chopped nuts together; pour half cake batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix together cinnamon and brown sugar and sprinkle over first half of batter.
Pour remaining batter in pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip; chill overnight.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake to package directions.
Use 9-inch pans.
Cool and split layers to make 4.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in a 325° oven as it heats.
Remove pan from oven and add crumbs.
Stir into butter. Mix and pat out in an even layer.
Sprinkel chips, coconut and nuts in evenly.
Carefully drizzle or spoon milk over all.	Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.	Partially cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, celery, grapes, salt and pepper.
Add the mayonnaise and sour cream and mix well.
Put into a salad bowl lined with lettuce leaves and sprinkle with the chopped walnuts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg pie
directions: Cook in glass pie dish or round glass pan in microwave 1 package of frozen broccoli or fresh broccoli until done.
Drain. Pour mixture over the broccoli and bake in oven at 350° until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 9 x 13 casserole, pour both cans of soup and mix with 1 cup of water. Stir in rice. Lay chicken breasts on top of rice mixture. Melt desired amount of margarine and pour over top. Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked and tender.

title: chocolate fudge candy
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and cook to the soft ball stage. Remove from the heat and add the butter or margarine.
Let cool and add the vanilla and nuts. Beat until fudge is thick and loses its gloss. Pour into greased pan and cut into squares.

title: cappuccino(lo-cal)
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, heat milk until tiny bubbles form around edge and mixture is hot (do not boil).
Carefully pour hot milk into blender or food processor, and blend at high speed until frothy.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt margarine; add milk and mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt next 3 ingredients; dip balls into chocolate mixture.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat until soft, butter; add gradually until creamy, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Sift before measuring and add flour.
Roll the dough into small balls.
Place them on a greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, then add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in tube pan at 350°.

title: vegetable saute
directions: In skillet, cook garlic in oil.
Add celery, pepper, mushrooms, oregano and Worcestershire sauce; cook until tender-crisp.
Add beans and carrots; heat through.
Put in a one-quart casserole dish and heat at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Place roll dough on 11 x 17-inch pan and stretch to fit pan. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix sour cream, salad dressing and cream cheese and spread over cooled crust.
Use 3/4 cup each of chopped broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, green onions, carrots, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Place on top of sour cream mixture and press vegetables down into mixture.
I put waxed paper over it and then press vegetables in with it.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini casserole #3(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Alternate layers of thin sliced zucchini, peppers, onion and tomatoes, throwing in a pinch of spices to taste on each layer.
Top last layer (or both) with shredded or sliced cheese.
Decorate top with a last few tomatoes and strips of bacon.
Bake, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Continue baking, uncovered, until bacon is crisp and vegetables are tender to taste.
Serve immediately or undercook slightly, then microwave before serving.

title: "ten minute" fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt cream cheese in saucepan.
Add light cream.
Stir in Parmesan cheese (over medium-low heat).
Serve over linguine.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crust:
Grease and flour glass baking dish.
Mix flour, margarine, brown sugar and pecans; press into bottom of dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: ham and swiss cheese quiche
directions: Combine eggs and milk for the basic custard.
Add Swiss cheese and ham.
Pour the custard mixture into a partially baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake in 325° oven for about 50 minutes or until center is nearly set.
(To prebake the pastry shell, place unpricked pie shell in 450° oven for 5 minutes.)

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Before adding chocolate bits, mix with mixer.
Then add bits; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend together.
Pack into a 4-cup mold and chill at least 3 hours.
Remove from mold and serve with crackers.

title: beefy enchiladas
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup cheese and onion; set aside.
Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Top each tortilla with 1 heaping tablespoon of meat mixture.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash
beans
and
soak
overnight.
Combine
remaining ingredients.
Bring to a
boil
on top of stove and let gently boil for 15 minutes.
Bake	in oven at 350° for about 6 hours. Keep beans covered with water at all times.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix together milk and cream of coconut.
Poke holes in hot cake with wooden spoon or spatula and pour in the mixture.
Cool.

title: no roll apple pie(easy and delicious)
directions: Anthony's favorite, especially the topping.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and salt.
Pour milk over them, stirring while pouring.
Place in double boiler and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats back of a spoon. Cool; strain.
Add cream and vanilla.
Freeze.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a deep 9-inch pie pan, combine beans, onion, mustard and sugar. Then place bacon strips on top of beans. Bake 25 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, chicken, sour cream, soup, chilies, onion, pepper and salt. Spoon about 1/2 cup onto center of tortilla; roll up. Place seam side down in a greased baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake a few minutes longer until cheese is melted. Let stand for 5 to 7 minutes before serving.

title: trisciut treats
directions: Top Triscuit with Swiss cheese, Mozzarella and pepperoni.
Put under broiler a few minutes until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour in greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour. Let cool completely.
Split cake to make 3 layers.

title: sweet potato loaf cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and water.
Beat at medium speed until mixed well.
In another bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in sweet potatoes, pecans and raisins.
Spoon batter into two greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Let cool in cans 10 minutes, then remove cans for further cooling.

title: funnel cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Mix egg and milk together.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Hold finger over hole in a funnel bottom and pour batter into the funnel.
Remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion into pan filled with 1-inch of hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove from pan and drain on a paper towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar and milk.
Add the melted butter.
Add the potatoes.
Mix and pour into a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg over the top and bake 30 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Slightly cook broccoli.
Saute chopped green pepper, celery and onion in margarine.
Mix together with remaining ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southwestern layered dip
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat cheese dip, cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Spread on serving plate. Drizzle with taco sauce.
Top with lettuce, onions, olives (if desired), tomato and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips and/or crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: diet salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Can be used for cole slaw or lettuce salad.

title: aunt lelia's canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix sugars, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently. Reduce heat.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Stir in juice.
Pack into hot jars 1/3 full with apple slices.
Pour in enough of the liquid to cover.
Remove air bubbles with rubber scraper.
Continue packing jars 1/3 at a time with apples and liquid.
Fill within 1-inch of top and seal. Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Put peeled, grated cucumber, onion and a little of the liquid in blender.
Add other ingredients.
Put in mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: cheesy eggplant
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add eggplant cubes and toss to coat. Saute until tender.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange tomatoes on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dawn's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in oleo. Add other ingredients. Mix together and pour into greased casserole. Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 400° until browned and bubbling hot (about 25 minutes). Serves 8.

title: white chocolate crunch(great for gifts or snacks)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Melt white chocolate in microwave. Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Pour onto wax paper in thin layer.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: cocoa peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat
oven to
Have
cookie
sheets
ready.
Mix flour, cocoa and baking
soda.
Beat
butter and peanut butter in a large bowl with electric mixer until creamy.
Add 1/3 cup granulated sugar and the brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg, milk and
vanilla
until
well blended.	With mixer on low speed gradually beat
in flour mixture just until blended. Shape heaping teaspoonfuls
into balls.
Roll in remaining 1/4 cup granulated sugar to
coat.
Place
1/2-inches
apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake
to
12 minutes until firm. Immediately place a chocolate
kiss
on each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks
around the edge.
Remove to racks to cool completely. Makes 48 cookies.

title: pudding pie(dessert)
directions: Stir pudding mixes in 6 cups of milk in large saucepan.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and starts to boil.
Pour into pie shell.
(Extra can be poured in styrofoam coffee cups for homemade pudding cups.)
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Top with Cool Whip and chocolate sprinkles.

title: cottage potatoes(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Peel potatoes and cube.
Salt and pepper.
Dice vegetables, cheese and bread and add to potatoes.
Pour melted butter over and mix.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: warmer kartoffelsalat(hot potato salad)
directions: About one hour before serving, cook potatoes in jacket with 1 teaspoon salt, until tender, about 35 minutes.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, flour, jello and food coloring until thick.
Pour over strawberries in baked pie shell.

title: overnight salad
directions: Alternate the first 4 ingredients (2 layers each).
Mix together the Miracle Whip and sugar.
Spread over top.
Sprinkle top of salad with the Parmesan cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Stir before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste, if necessary.
May sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and quick oats. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: apple and sweet potato casserole
directions: Place 1/2 potato slices in 2-quart casserole bowl or 8 x 10-inch pan.
Arrange half of apple slices, then rest of potato and rest of apples.
Combine syrup, butter and salt.
Pour over potatoes and apples.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove cover and continue to bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender, basting frequently.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Stir in beans. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Store in cool place in airtight container.

title: corn and zucchini casserole
directions: Place zucchini, water and salt in covered pan; steam about 10 minutes, until tender.
Drain and chop or grind zucchini.
Saute pepper, onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until onion is transparent.
Add zucchini, remaining butter, corn, cheese and eggs.
Mix well and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate. Garnish with strawberries.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Chop vegetables by hand for best results. Blend mayo and cream cheese. Fold in vegetables. Mix together 1 day before serving.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Put sugar, salt and mustard in a jar.
Pack cucumbers in jar. Cover with cold vinegar.
Seal.
Use after 6 weeks.

title: country brunch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and blend well.
Pour mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and refrigerate, covered, 8 hours or overnight. Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a small bowl stir together sugar, cocoa powder, and flour. In a medium saucepan melt butter or margarine.
Stir in cocoa mixture until thoroughly mixed and no lumps are visible. Gradually add milk to saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 1 minute more.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Serve warm over biscuits.

title: cheese and chives potato
directions: Mix cottage cheese with a fork until smooth.
Add chives, vinegar, salt and pepper. Stuff baked potato.

title: hummingbird cake(1 to 3 layer cake)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and banana.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting and sprinkle pecans on top.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on frozen package.
Drain.
In a saucepan melt half the margarine or butter.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Place vegetables in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour sauce mix over them and mix lightly.
Top with shredded cheese.
Melt the remaining butter; toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well butter, cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar. Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate drops and 1/2 block of wax.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Let set on wax paper.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Flour chicken and then brown in skillet.
Take chicken out and drain grease out of pan.
Put chicken back in skillet and add tomatoes and chopped onion.
Fill skillet up with water until it covers chicken.
Add rice.
Put on medium heat for 1 hour and let simmer.
Be sure to stir while it simmers.

title: ham loaf or ham balls
directions: Mix together and form into loaf or balls.
Baste with sauce.

title: green enchiladas
directions: In skillet, brown beef, onions, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add Cheddar cheese and 1/2 of chilies to meat.
Set aside.
Heat together soup, American cheese, milk and remaining green chilies. Roll meat mixture into tortillas and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over tortillas and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Spread flattened dough with the ingredients.
Roll up and pinch edges.
Rub with olive oil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
together
sausage, biscuit mix and flour.	Roll in small balls.
Bake
at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool; store in tightly covered container.	Makes 3 dozen servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl.
Lightly grease round cake pan. Pour ingredients into pan.
Place in preheated oven at 350°. Cook for 1 hour.

title: reese's cups (bars)
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Mix all together well and pat onto cookie sheet or long cake pan.
Boil for 1 minute Milnot, sugar and 1/2 cup butter. Add 1/2 to 3/4 package chocolate chips.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Mix with apples.
Dot with butter.
Pour into pie crust; top with other pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: Boil fish in water.
Saute onion until golden brown.
Add to stock.
Add cubed potatoes and cook until potatoes are soft.
Add milk, butter and seasoning.
Serves 6.

title: santa claus milk
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard cinnamon stick and cloves.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add 2 tablespoons cold milk, stirring until smooth.
Add to hot milk, stirring constantly.
Cook about 2 minutes (do not boil).
Pour into mugs and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Season with onion, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Add instant rice and water to make enough for your family. Cook until rice is done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: chocolate mint icebox pie
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add peppermint extract, vanilla and baking chocolate.
Spread in graham cracker or vanilla wafer crust.
Let set at least 6 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: slow-cooked sunday chicken
directions: Place chicken (whole or pieces) in a slow cooker, on rack if desired.
Add water to cooker.
Mix together remaining ingredients except cornstarch and spoon over chicken.
Cover cooker and cook slowly 2 to 3 hours, until very tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter.

title: broccoli salad 2
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.

title: roasted red pepper bread
directions: About 15 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
With serrated knife, cut Italian bread crosswise into 12 slices.
Place slices on cookie sheet.
Spread slices with butter or margarine and sprinkle with roasted red pepper and oregano leaves.
Bake bread until golden, about 7 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, about 165 calories per serving.

title: myrene's spaghetti and cheese
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix with cheese, pimento, mushroom soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all together in mixing bowl.
Put in a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cooled, sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet; saute mushrooms until tender and set aside.
Place rice in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add hot chicken broth, water chestnuts, salt and remaining 2 tablespoons butter, cut in small pieces.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir in sauteed mushrooms; cover and continue to bake 15 to 30 minutes longer, or until moisture is absorbed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and sugar.
Add oil and mix well.
Add eggs.
Add buttermilk gradually.
Add figs, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
While hot, pour sauce over cake in pan.
Cool, then turn cake over to put on plate.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oats, water and milk in a large bowl.
Let stand 20 minutes.
In the meantime, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. After the 20 minutes are up, add to the oatmeal mixture.
Combine all other ingredients except the flour and stir well.
Stir in 3 cups of flour and mix.
Continue to add flour until a workable dough is obtained.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead for about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and shape into 2 loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Allow to rise again and then bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, powder, salt, sugar, soda and cinnamon. Add rolled oats and raisins and mix together and in order, shortening, eggs and milk.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet, about 1 1/2-inches apart. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: planked beef with fiesta patties
directions: Combine beef with salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 to 8 patties, 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Set oven for broiling.
Place patties under broiler 2 to 3-inches from heat.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes, then remove.
Top with catsup, cheese and green pepper.
Put on platter.
Spoon mashed potatoes around the patties.
Brush with melted butter.
Return to broiler until potatoes are browned and cheese is melted, about 3 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: steak diane(4 servings)
directions: Pound steaks to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle each side of steak with salt, pepper and 1/8 teaspoon of dry mustard; pour into meat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add meat; cook for 2 minutes on each side.
Transfer meat to hot serving plate.
To skillet, add lemon juice, chives and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boiling; pour over meat.
Garnish with cooked mushrooms.

title: egg casserole
directions: Scramble eggs to moist stage.
Season with salt and pepper; add parsley.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle bacon over eggs.
Chill, covered, for several hours or overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: homemade beef salami(no casing required)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and knead until well blended.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 3 days; reknead once each day.
On fourth day, shape mixture into 4 log shape rolls. Place logs on a rack with pan below to catch fat.
Fat cooks out of meat.
Put into oven set at 150° for 8 hours.
Turn logs after first 3 hours.
Store in refrigerator.
Hmmm good!

title: rabbit stew
directions: Cut up the rabbit into serving size pieces.
Cook in water until tender.
Add carrots, onions, celery and potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste and thicken with a thin paste of flour and water.

title: smoky bacon wraps
directions: Cut each bacon strip in half widthwise.
Wrap one piece of bacon around each sausage.
Place in a foil-lined 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, at 400 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until bacon is crisp and sausage is heated through.
Yield:
About 3 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until done at 350°.

title: natilla christmas dessert
directions: Dissolve the cornstarch in the milk.
Add the brown sugar. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When the sugar is melted and begins to thicken, add the cinnamon and coconut.
When the natilla is very thick, pour onto a large serving dish.

title: party meat balls 'n sauce(serves a crowd)
directions: Mix the ground beef, egg, onion, garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Form into marble-size meat balls.
Brown and drain on paper towels.
Warm the chili sauce and grape jelly to melt jelly.
Add meat balls and simmer 30 minutes.

title: pasta and spinach toss
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Stir in garlic.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms and onion are soft (5 to 7 minutes). Stir in spinach.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (3 to 4 minutes).
Drain fettuccine.
Return fettuccine to saucepan; stir in spinach mixture.
Remove to serving platter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cider-citrus cheer(microwave)
directions: In large glass bowl, combine all ingredients.
Heat in microwave on High for 9 minutes, then on Medium-low for 8 minutes. Strain into pitcher.
Serve hot.
Garnish individual drinks with cocktail picks speared with fresh cranberries and an accordian strip of lemon peel.

title: 3-bean salad with macaroni
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together well. Add oil. Stir and pour over all other ingredients.
Stir to coat.
Refrigerate.
Keeps for several days.

title: texas barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket and all items in plastic bag.
Shake and rotate for 4 hours in refrigerator, then remove from marinade while coals are warming, grill for 15 minutes.
Save marinade.
Wrap brisket in heavy foil, allowing room for the marinade to be poured on brisket through small hole.
Seal up tight.
Grill 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning occasionally.
To serve, slice diagonally across grain in thin slices.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: baked pork chops and baked beans
directions: Mix salt, pepper, brown sugar, catsup and mustard.
Pour mixture over pork chops and top with onion.
Bake at 350° for
1 1/4 hours.

title: louella's luscious - raw apple cake
directions: Add sugar into apples; stir.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well (by hand) together.
Place mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: cloverleaf luncheon rolls
directions: Break yeast into 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Let stand 10 minutes. Make dough of flour, sugar, salt, butter and milk.
When lukewarm, add flour and yeast.
Beat until smooth.
Cover bowl.
Place in pan of warm water until dough is double its size.
Add enough sifted flour to stiffen.
Turn on floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Rub with soft butter.
Place in greased bowl.
Place bowl in pan of warm water.
Cover until mixture is double its size.
Place on lightly floured board.
Cut dough in pieces size of marble.
Dip in melted butter.
Place three in well-greased muffin tins.
Cover. Let rise to double its size.
Bake in quick oven 15 to 20 minutes in 400° to 425° oven.
Brush with butter when out of oven.
This will make 1 1/2 to 2 dozen rolls.

title: betty's blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Refrigerate until jello sets.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla together and mix well.
Spread onto jello and add pecans.

title: easy tapas
directions: Rinse and trim asparagus spears. Cut ham into thirds vertically. Wrap ham third around asparagus. Place each wrapped spear on sprayed broiler proof pan or dish. Drizzle light olive oil over spears. Sprinkle lightly with sea salt (optional). Broil spears until ham begins to crisp, then rotate and broil until done (about 2 to 3 minutes each side).

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni noodles.
Chop green pepper and onion. Mix all ingredients.
(May have to add more mayonnaise.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Uncover last few minutes so top will get crisp.

title: lillian's chocolate pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar; add cocoa and flour, and mix well. Gradually add milk; mix thoroughly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour into cooled pie shell and top with meringue. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden.

title: ground beef marsala(280 calories per serving)
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, on waxed paper, shape ground beef into 8 flat, oval patties.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook patties and onion until patties are browned on both sides, about 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, Marsala and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, and turning patties once.
To serve, pour sauce over patties.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bonnie's taco salad appetizer
directions: Brown ground beef and cook with taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Spread seasoned beef on bottom of a
9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Drop teaspoonfuls of sour cream over beef. Sprinkle cheese on top to form even layer.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender.
Drain and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add margarine, sour cream, onion, soup and chestnuts. Put one-half of the mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle one-half of the cheese and repeat layers. Top with crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil oleo in water.
Add flour and beat hard until it forms a ball.
Add egg, one at a time.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Blend pudding with milk; add softened cream cheese, let set 15 minutes.
Spread over cooled crust and top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle small amount of shaved chocolate or Hershey's syrup over top.
Refrigerate.

title: ruby apple cake
directions: Dice apples; break eggs over them.
Add sugar, cinnamon, oil and nuts.
Mix well with a fork.
Sift flour with salt and baking soda.
Mix with apple mixture.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 55 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: mom's raw apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine apples, sugar and raisins; let stand for 10 minutes, until syrup forms.
Then add in oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well with apple mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: taste like hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water. Let sit.

title: blueberry cake(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° in greased, floured pan (9 x 11-inch) for 45 minutes.

title: robyn's macaroni-cheese and hamburger dish
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Add cheese sauce, milk and salt.
Add hamburger; mix well.
(Note:
More cheese can be added, if desired.)

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces.
Add sugar, spices and butter. Place on top of stove and heat.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with crust.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cook in bottom of oven.
The fruit will cook while pastry browns.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Cut slices in half, set aside.
In a jar with a tight-fitting lid;
combine the oil, honey, vinegar, soy sauce and the reserved juice;
shake well. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes;
combine the romaine, onion slices and pineapple slices in a serving dish.
Drizzle with dressing, toss to coat.
Serves 6.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove.
Stir in chips until melted. Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla; beat until blended.
Pour into a greased pan.
Top with walnut halves.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Makes 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaves.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: raspberry coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to
Grease
and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. In small bowl combine 1/3 cup of chopped walnuts, sugar, flour and butter.
Set
aside.
In large bowl combine cake mix, sour cream, water and
eggs at low speed until moistened, then beat at highest speed for 2 minutes.
Spoon 3 cups batter into pan; spread raspberry
filling over batter.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup remaining walnuts.
Spread
remaining
batter over.
Sprinkle nut mixture evenly
over
batter.
Bake
at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until
toothpick
in center comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: melon and prosciutto
directions: Cut melon lengthwise into halves; scoop out seeds and fibers. Cut each half lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Remove rind.
Cut crosswise slits 1 1/2-inch apart in each melon wedge.
Cut Prosciutto into 1-inch strips; place several strips Prosciutto over each wedge pushing it into slits.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, salt and milk; beat slightly.
Melt some butter in a frying pan.
Dip one slice of bread at a time in mixture then brown in frying pan on both sides.	You can top with jelly, syrup or powdered sugar.

title: party pork chops
directions: Place unsalted chops in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make sauce of other ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: make your own peanut butter
directions: Peel skins off nuts and put them in blender.
Grind to a paste while adding oil, a little at a time, until peanut butter is desired consistency.
Add salt to taste.
Refrigerate in covered jar.
The oil may rise to the top.
Re-stir before using.

title: fiesta barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Arrange chicken breasts in large baking dish. Top with diced tomatoes and peppers. Pour barbecue sauce over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is no longer pink. The sauce is great poured over French fries.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine until golden.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add lima beans and mix well with tomato mixture.
Turn into casserole dish.
Toss bread crumbs with Parmesan cheese and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° or until topping is well browned.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Simmer carrots, celery and green onions in 2 cans of chicken broth.
Saute onion in oleo and add flour and milk to make a white sauce.
Combine these ingredients and add Cheez Whiz.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: homemade ice cream(hand crank or electric)
directions: Add first 5 ingredients into metal container.
Chop fruit in food processor.
Add fruit to metal container.
Add enough milk to reach fill line.
Place mixer in container and cover.
Put in bucket and a layer of ice, a layer of rock salt and 1 cup water. Repeat layers until bucket is full.

title: easy fudge
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook the milk and sugar; bring to a rolling boil, then lower heat.
Keep stirring and boiling for 13 to 14 minutes.
(This gets yellowish.)
Pour boiled mixture over mix in bowl.
Stir with a wooden spoon real well.
Melt all chips and marshmallows.
Spread on a cookie sheet with sides.
Do not refrigerate.
Set for 24 hours before cutting.

title: apple cider
directions: Mix together in pan and heat.
Serve hot.

title: raisin bread(sugar-free)
directions: *Whip chopped fresh or canned pears in a food processor or blender until smooth.

title: chocolate angel torte
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Melt chocolate bits over double boiler.
Separate eggs and add beaten yolks to melted chocolate.
Beat whites until stiff.
Beat cream until stiff, then mix together and add chocolate mixture.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and put 1/2 of cake pieces in bottom spread with 1/2 of sauce mixture and 1/2 of sliced nuts.
Repeat, ending with nuts.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat
oven
Have
cookie sheets ready.
With wooden spoon
stir
peanut
butter, sugar and eggs in a medium size
bowl until thoroughly blended.	With floured hands roll level measuring
tablespoonfuls into 1 1/4 inch balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until cookies look dry with tops cracked.
Remove from oven and press
a
chocolate kiss in center of each.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 to 2 minutes;
remove to wire racks to cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cream cheese, vanilla and Cool Whip. Whip until fluffy.
Mix pudding and milk and add to cream cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Crush 1/2 package Oreo cookies (food processor works best) and place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread mixture on top.
Crush rest of Oreo cookies and spread over top of mixture.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: cheese sandwich spread
directions: Grind all together.
Mix with 1/4 cup mayonnaise.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan, put sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and peanut butter.
Heat, melt until it comes to a full boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Mix together oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Add to peanut butter mixture, mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on aluminum foil.
Cool and enjoy.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Spread cottage cheese in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Cook ground beef; drain any excess grease.
Stir in 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, salt, oregano and tomato paste.
Spoon over the cottage cheese.
Stir milk, eggs and Bisquick mix together until blended; pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 1 or 2 minutes more, until cheese is melted.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocado with fork and then add sour cream, tomatoes, chiles, lime juice and garlic salt.
Blend well.
Save the seed, if desired, and put it in dip right before you serve this.
Serve with raw vegetables or tortilla chips.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and add to salad.

title: cheesy tuna crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine tuna and 2 tablespoons cheese. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place about 3 tablespoons tuna mixture on wide end of each triangle.
Roll up; start at shortest side of triangle and roll to opposite point.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on greased baking sheets.
(These may be frozen and place in freezer bags to be used later.)
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pepper hash
directions: Chop or grind first 4 ingredients completely.
Combine 1/2 cup vinegar and 1 cup water; bring to boil.
Pour over drained vegetables; let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add 1 cup vinegar, 1 1/2 cups sugar, salt and whole mustard seed.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over pepper hash and fill sterile jars.
Process with hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 pints.

title: microwave spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cook on 50 for 15 minutes or until hot.
Remove spices.
Serve hot, garnished with slices of red apples, if desired.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, water, and vanilla until creamy. In a separate bowl, mix oats and flour.
Add oats and flour mixture slowly to other mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
(For variety, add chopped nuts, raisins, chocolate chips, or coconut).
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Drop by funnel into hot vegetable oil.
Turn once to brown both sides.
Top with confectioners sugar or desired topping.

title: hershey bar pound cake
directions: Melt candy in syrup in a double boiler; cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; add to chocolate mixture.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternating with buttermilk.

title: lemon salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the hot water and set aside to cool. When nearly congealed, add the cherries, pineapple, grapes, celery and marshmallows.
Chill well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and cook until transparent, slowly. Add Dijon mustard and flour.
Stir.
Put in 8 cups of bouillon, already dissolved.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, toast croutons and dry out.
Pour soup into crocks, place croutons on top, then slice of Mozzarella cheese, then sprinkle a little Parmesan cheese on top.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve hot!!!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased baking dish.

title: greek pasta salad(yield: 6 servings)
directions: Combine cooled pasta, cucumber and Feta cheese in a large serving bowl; set aside.
Combine oil, Parmesan, oregano and lemon juice in 2 cup measuring cup or small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over pasta and toss to coat all ingredients.
Best when served immediately at room temperature, but can be stored in refrigerator and served cold.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Prepare Minute rice in broth leftover from cooked chicken by package directions.
Debone chicken.
Mix well the chicken, soups, onion, parsley and pepper.
Layer rice and chicken mixture alternately until all is used.

title: okra and tomato gumbo
directions: Cut okra into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook onions and green pepper in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Blend in sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Add the 3 tomatoes and then the okra.
Cook over low heat and, when it comes to boil, simmer 1/2 hour or more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Remove half the crumbs and half the cheese for topping.
Fold remaining ingredients together.
Pour into large buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with reserved cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini al dente.
Drain.
Let cool for a short time (15 minutes).
Then add Good Seasons dressing (already prepared in salad dressing bottle).
Then mix in remaining ingredients.
Serve well chilled.

title: savory pilaf
directions: Cook rice according to package directions (don't use salt or butter).
Substitute the bouillon cube.
While rice cooks, melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion, celery, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Cook over medium heat (stir several times) until celery is almost tender.
Gently add cooked rice, sage, cereal, basil, pepper and water.
Cover and cook over very low heat about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch dish. Bake 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chili-chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken and next 3 ingredients in hot oil in a Dutch oven until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and next 5 ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Top individual servings with remaining ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6.
May be served over rice.
Super good!

title: mexitalian lasagna
directions: In a large bowl combine chili, drained salsa, mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
In a small bowl, combine cottage cheese and parsley flakes.
Cook noodles according to package.
In greased or oiled 9 x 9-inch baking dish, layer noodles, chili, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry dreams
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, brandy extract and lemon juice, mixing until well-blended.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Use a 2-quart casserole.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower until done.
Pour water off Veg-All.
Add Veg-All and soups.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all these ingredients together, except the wax and chocolate chips).
Then roll into small balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips together in double boiler.
Dip the balls and let dry on wax paper.
Makes about 7 to 8 dozen balls.

title: thousand island dressing(for salad)
directions: Combine
all ingredients together and mix well.
May be doubled or tripled and kept in the refrigerator for later use. Very
good	on
quartered
head
of
lettuce.
Cut	lettuce in wedges, pour the Thousand Island dressing on top and serve.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Combine berries, sugar and lemon juice. Let stand 30 minutes. Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water. Add to berry mixture and chill until partially set. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into your favorite pie crust, plain or graham cracker. Chill until set. This recipe makes one 10-inch pie or two 7-inch pies. Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: pancake and waffle syrup
directions: Add brown sugar and water in saucepan. Add salt and Karo syrup; mix all ingredients in saucepan. Bring to boil and boil for 10 minutes. May add maple flavoring if desired to taste. Pour over waffles, pancakes, French toast...

title: chestnut meatballs
directions: Combine bread crumbs, milk, soy sauce, garlic and onion.
Add meats and water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: black bean and chicken soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Put them into a large bowl and cover completely with cold water.
Let stand overnight!
Drain beans.
Transfer to a medium pan.
Add 2 cups water and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook 15 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes, until beans are tender.
Drain and discard the bay leaf.

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix flour and shortening. Add buttermilk and mix. Add enough flour to work as a biscuit dough. Roll out in 2 portions real thin and cut in squares. Cut butter into small pieces and put 4 or 5 pieces on each dough square. Cover with sugar and drops of vanilla. Roll and pinch sides and ends. Put in buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: country biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, sift together flour and baking powder.
Make a well in flour mixture; add salad dressing and buttermilk.
Stir with fork until dough forms a ball. Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chocolate pies(two)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add milk and egg yolks. Cook until thick.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) pie shells.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain and chop fruits.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add concentrate and stir until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in whipped topping and fold in fruit.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and slice.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Whisk together all ingredients except rice in the top of a double boiler over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 8 minutes until custard has thickened to the consistency of a heavy cream.
Do not allow custard to boil.
Pour custard through strainer and chill.
Cook rice separately; when cool, blend with custard.
Add Cool Whip and chill.

title: apple pizza pie
directions: Roll and spread crust on pizza pan.
Slice apples on crust. Flavor with 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Top with 3/4 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; let set in warm oven for 15 minutes.

title: ponettone
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to egg whites, then add all dry ingredients, adding flour last.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Bake in cast-iron pan, greased and floured.

title: apricot mold (jello)
directions: Cook pineapple and jello for 12 minutes.
Boil.
Stir not to stick.
Take off stove to cool.
Beat cream cheese into jello mixture.
Use electric mixer until smooth.
Add celery and nuts and stir.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into greased mold (grease with mayo).
Refrigerate 1 to 4 days ahead or 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: noreen's peanut butter cups
directions: You will also need bonbon paper cups.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Add milk or cream and chopped nuts.
Drop on waxed paper until cool.
Then in a double boiler, melt Hershey bar and paraffin.
Dip pieces of candy in chocolate. Ready to eat.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Arrange in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (or Pam spray).
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese, then top with bread cubes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix lime in 1 gal. of water and soak cucumbers overnight using crockery or enamel ware. (Do not use aluminum containers.) Drain and wash cucumbers; soak in ice water 2 or 3 hours. Mix together sugar, vinegar, water, salt and heat. Place pickling spices and celery seed in a bag made of cheese cloth. Add cucumbers and bagged spices. Cook 40-45 minutes. Remove spice bag and put in clean sterile jars. Seal in jars while still hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in a greased casserole dish in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, remove from bone, cut into pieces.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch buttered dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and combine with poppy seed.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar. Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs into sugar mix one at a time and add to flour mixture.
Add chocolate morsels and chopped nuts.
Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; saut onions and bell peppers until onions are clear. Add flour and mix well. Cover and cool for 15 minutes; stir occasionally. Add parsley and shrimp; cook for 20 minutes, stirring often. Add cream of mushroom soup, cheese, peppers and garlic; mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook covered on low for 20 minutes. Cook noodles and drain. Add noodles to sauce and stir well. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Stuff green chilies with Jack cheese and roll up.
Place in greased, shallow 12 x 8-inch pan, seam side down.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm with crackers, chips or Syrian bread.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Cook ground sausage and ground beef.
Add seasonings.
Melt in Velveeta cheese, etc. and mix well.
Spread a spoonful of mixture on each slice of party bread.
Put on cookie sheet and toast for 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Bring water to boil with beef cube and butter.
Stir in rice. Cover and cook 18 to 20 minutes.
Stir in parsley, onion and carrot.
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.

title: pork chops braised
directions: Combine sage, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper.
Press this mixture into both sides of each pork chop.

In a heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet, melt butter with olive oil over moderate heat. When foam subsides, place chops in pan and brown for 2 to 3 minutes on each side. When chops are golden brown, remove from pan and pour off
all but a thin film of fat from pan. Add the wine and parsley and bring to a boil. Return chops to pan, cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Baste with pan juices occasionally. Cook for 25 to 30 minutes, making sure they are fully cooked. Reserve liquid and pour over chops when served.
Serve on a bed of white rice.

title: "economic" ham salad
directions: Grind bologna
and eggs.
Add the relish and mayonnaise to desired
consistency
for spreading on sandwich bread.
May use more or less relish to taste.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans.
Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges.
Pour into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Combine pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip.
Spread between layers, and on sides and top.
Refrigerate.

title: oreo cookie pudding
directions: Mix pudding by box directions in a large bowl.
Mix together cream cheese and 1 bowl Cool Whip until smooth.
Crumble all but 10 of the cookies into mixture; stir until mixed well.
Spread out into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until mixture is set.
Spread 1 bowl Cool Whip on top.
Decorate with remaining cookies.
Serve cold.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Cook over medium heat, sugar and juice of 2 oranges, adding water to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil.
Brush over cake and let soak in.
Refrigerate 3 days.
Is also good to eat hot.

title: copper pennies salad
directions: Cook carrots until crisp and tender.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 12 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple in bowl.
Add cherries, dates and nuts. Sprinkle pudding over top and fold in rest of ingredients; refrigerate.

title: small tart quiches
directions: Recipe makes 4 or 5 tarts. Saute first 3 ingredients; put small amount in bottom of each tart. Next, add meat. Beat eggs with milk and pour over pepper mixture and meat until covered. Top with Cheddar cheese. Pop in 375° oven and cook until puffed up and golden brown.

title: macaroni skillet supper
directions: In large skillet brown meat, add onions, celery, pepper and saute
until brown.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Add
macaroni, cover and cook over low heat until tender, stirring
occasionally, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in
Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and let
stand
for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer garden peas, top with layer of asparagus tips, top with cream of mushroom soup and sprinkle pimento over the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: evelyn's pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together until creamy.
Alternate 2 eggs and 1/2 cup flour until all are mixed together well.
Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Grease and flour pan.

title: brad's favorite dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter, pecans and brown sugar.
Spread onto the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan (makes a thin crust layer).	Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled pecan mixture.
Mix 2 puddings together with milk until thick.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle grated Hershey bar on top.

title: tuna toss salad
directions: Drain tuna; break into large pieces.
Combine carrot, pineapple, celery, mayonnaise, raisins and tuna.
Mix lightly. Serve on salad greens.
Garnish with carrot curls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken wings korean style
directions: Remove tips of wings and disjoint.
Dredge in flour and fry in hot oil.
Combine sour sauce, sugar, garlic powder, green onions, red peppers and sesame seed.
Bring to a boil, then simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken wings and serve at room temperature.

title: choc-o-nut bars
directions: In large bowl, cream together brown sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Add salt, baking soda and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread in 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Yields approximately 75 squares.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream well the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla flavoring. Sift dry ingredients together and blend into creamed mixture. Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and apple.
Add sugar and marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add Cool Whip just before serving.

title: one pan brownies
directions: Melt together the butter and chocolate squares.
Add vanilla, sugar and beaten eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt and nuts.

title: orange pecan pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil and debone chicken breasts.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Layer broccoli and chicken in casserole. Top with chicken, soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Cover with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water to make smooth paste.
Boil until it forms a hard ball in water.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Remove candy from stove and beat into egg whites, pouring very slowly. Add nuts after it begins to grain or get real stiff.
Place on wax paper or buttered plate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form small balls.
Place on cookie sheet 1 to 2 inches apart.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chickens until they almost drop to pieces.
Cut in pieces a little larger than for salad.
To 3 pints of the broth, add onion, salt and tomatoes.
Bring to boil; add spaghetti and cook 20 minutes.
Add milk, eggs, cheese and tomato sauce and cook 15 minutes.
Add chicken and Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces. Serves many.

title: peach crisp
directions: Combine flour, white sugar, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix all the ingredients, except egg together, then add 1 unbeaten egg with a fork until crumbly.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown
meat
in oil in a big kettle.
Add water, tomato sauce, onion,
garlic, celery, parsley and seasonings.
Cover and simmer
for
hours.
Add zucchini, peas and spaghetti. Simmer for
minutes
or longer until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if so desire before serving.

title: gehaktballen
directions: Mix hamburger meat, eggs, pepper and salt together in a bowl. Add parsley flakes.
Make 4-inch balls out of it.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in a pan.

title: all at once spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add ground beef.
Cook, stirring, until meat loses red color.
Drain off fat.
Add seasonings.
Pour in tomato paste and water; bring to a boil.

title: corn, avocado and crab dip
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add corn. Return to a boil and cook 4 minutes. Drain in a colander; chill corn under cold running water. Cut kernels off cobs with sharp knife (about 2 cups). Mix onion, lime juice and salt in a large bowl. Let stand about 10 minutes.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer rice, corn, 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water, the onion, green pepper and ground beef. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour second can of tomato sauce diluted with 1/4 can water over all.
Cover with bacon strips. Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocoa pink cuplets
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and salt. Cream together the sugar and shortening. Blend in unbeaten eggs and vanilla. Combine the soda and cold water. Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Blend thoroughly after each addition. Fill 20 to 24 muffin pans lined with baking cup half full. Sprinkle the chocolate chips and nuts over cupcake batter. Nuts are optional. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While hot, poke holes in cake and pour caramel topping.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk and spread over cooled cake.
Crush candy bars and sprinkle over cake.
Chill overnight.

title: chocolate chip whole wheat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg, water and vanilla; beat well.
Combine whole wheat flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, dried apricots and mini chip chocolates.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve with crackers or potato chips.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Place chops in a slow

cooker; sprinkle with salt, if desired and pepper. Add the onions, celery, green pepper and tomatoes. Combine ketchup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and bouillon. Pour over vegetables. Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours. Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water until smooth. Stir into liquid in slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 30 minutes or until thickened. Serve over rice.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat egg yolk and
add
oil
a
drop
at
a
time while beating egg.
When mixture begins to thicken add vinegar, then slowly add oil again.
When thick again add herbs.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in one bowl.
In a second bowl, combine all other ingredients just until mixed; add blueberries. Pour into greased muffin pans or paper lined muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks; combine in a small bowl with remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended and smooth.
With a spoon or pastry tube, fill center of each egg white.
Sprinkle lightly with additional paprika.
Chill, covered. Makes 16 deviled eggs.

title: punch
directions: For best results have all juices and ginger ale chilled prior to mixing.

title: annie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine first four ingredients and pour into a buttered 2 quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over macaroni mixture. Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve hot.

title: toni's supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cover inside large bowl with flour. Place bread in bowl.
Cover with dish towel.
Let rise.
Flour counter.
Roll dough (not too thin).
Mix all other ingredients and spread on dough.
Roll dough up, fold and pinch edges.
Place on cookie sheet.
For shiny look, baste with 1 egg white.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add sour cream, butter and muffin mix.
Add corn and mix well.
Bake at 350°
about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate glazed triple layer cheese cake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; blend well. Press onto bottom and 2 inches up side of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: kraut balls
directions: Mix together corned beef, cream cheese and kraut.
Roll into small balls and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.
Roll in flour; dip in cream.
Roll into cornflake crumbs and deep fry.

title: dream bars
directions: Combine ingredients in 8-inch square dish.
Microwave on Simmer 10 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool, cut into bars.

title: bob's basic oat-bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups or spray with Pam.
Fill 3/4 full with batter.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes. Makes 12 regular or 24 small muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Cover top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas baked beans
directions: Brown meat and drain any grease; add soup mix, mustard, vinegar, catsup and water.
Mix well.
Add beans; mix well again and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until boiling.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar, cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Cool.

title: southern dumplings
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder together.
Put in the shortening and gradually add about 2/3 cup chicken broth until a stiff dough results.
Roll out on a floured board and cut into strips 1-inch wide and 2 to 2 1/2-inches long.
