Bring remaining chicken broth to
a boil.
Drop a few strips at a time into broth. Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in ovenproof casserole. Heat through at 325°.
Top with French fried onion rings (canned) before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.
May be doubled.

title: chocolate caramel apples
directions: Wash and dry apples; remove stems.
Insert wooden stick or skewer into stem of each apple; set aside.
In saucepan, heat Milk Duds, milk, butter and vanilla over low heat, stirring constantly, until candy has melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat. Dip apples into candy mixture, one at a time, turning to coat evenly.
Allow excess candy mixture to drip back into pan.
Roll coated apples in nuts.
Transfer to buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except last 2. Top with crackers crumbs and walnuts. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit and nut cookies
directions: Cut fruits in small pieces.
Chop nuts.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Sift again over fruits and nuts.
Mix.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs together and then add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour over fruit and nut mixture.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt in a bowl and add to first mixture.
Roll dough in hands; roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Don't grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, but check.
Do not overbake; cookies will not look brown at all, just set.
Makes just 3 dozen.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 box Stove Top in pan; layer turkey, then 1/2 box stuffing on top of meat.
Mix on stove 2 cups chicken broth, 1/4 cup margarine, package of seasoning from stuffing and soups.
Bake until thick at 350°, about 45 minutes.

title: rosita's zesty salsa
directions: Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill at least two hours before serving.
Store covered for up to a week.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use 3 bouillon cubes to boil chicken.
Put onion and parsley flakes in water.
Use 1 cup broth and simmer onion and celery until tender.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine ingredients and press into a rectangular pan.

title: chicken and rice with "style"
directions: Place chicken in dish.
Cut up tomatoes on top of chicken; pour 1/2 can water over this.
Sprinkle dill weed over top; add mushrooms.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over hot white rice.

title: apricot freezer jam from zucchini
directions: Mix all ingredients in sauce pan and boil for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add jell-O.
Mix and let stand until cool. Freeze in appropriate containers.

title: chicken pot pie in never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Other beans may be substituted.

title: dave's cheezie wheaties
directions: Place one square of cheese on each cracker.
Microwave 12 seconds.
Add pepper, garlic powder, salt and bacon bits. Microwave 24 seconds.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and garlic.
In a casserole dish, mix the meat mixture with the baked beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Combine the ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard and salt in a small bowl.
Pour over meat and bean mixture.
Warm for one hour in a 325° oven.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and celery in butter.
Arrange chicken in layer, then layer of noodles.
Combine soup, broth, lemon juice, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over noodles.
Scatter mushrooms over top.
Bring to boil, then gently stir until noodles are tender.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy shrimp gumbo jubilee
directions: Brown flour in drippings and make roux.
Add onions, celery and garlic; brown for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, broth, salt and pepper.
Boil for 1 hour over medium heat.
Add shrimp, crab, oysters and okra.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Add Worcestershire.
Stir well and serve over rice.

title: eggplant dip(lebanese side dish and dip)
directions: Place eggplant on rack in tray and prick the skin with a fork several places.
Cook eggplant under broiler or on stove (on high), turning on all sides, until soft.
Test with a fork. Remove and peel under running water.
Place the peeled eggplant in a bowl.
Mash with a potato masher or garlic mallet.
In a small bowl, crush the garlic with the salt.
Add the tahini, water and mix.
Add the lemon and stir to mix well.
Add this to the mashed eggplant and mix very well.
Adjust salt and lemon to taste. Serve in deep platter.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Pour olive oil on top, if desired.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix.
Bring to a boil and pour over the following drained vegetables:

title: lamb shish kebab
directions: Cut leg of lamb into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Remove fat. Marinate in mixture of ingredients for 4 to 24 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add the 2 soups, chili beans, tomatoes and some of the cheese.
Using an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, pour mixture over chips; top with more cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill for several hours before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: venison jerky
directions: Marinate strips of venison about 1/4-inch thick overnight in covered glass bowl or container.
Drain strips and put them on cookie sheets.
Bake at 250°, turning twice until done, several hours.
Keep unrefrigerated.

title: tortillas
directions: Equal cups of flour and Bisquick mixed with enough water to make it of a bread dough consistency.
If sticky, add more Bisquick and flour.
After mixed, knead dough.
Roll dough into 1/2-cup balls and roll out on floured surface until about 1/8-inch thick.
Heat on hot griddle.
It only takes about 20 to 30 minutes on both sides.

title: french dressing(here's another good dressing recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix salt, pepper, dry mustard and egg yolk. Add oil and vinegar and whip.
Add chopped scallions, if desired. Keep refrigerated.

title: banana nut bars
directions: Mix together and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: fettucine verde
directions: Cook pasta in water until al dente; drain.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into loaf pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix thoroughly, pour into loaf pan and bake at 325° until tester comes out clean.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; add it to the pork and beans.
(The beans can be cooked either in the oven or a crock-pot.) Mix a small amount of mustard and brown sugar into a jar (8 ounces) of barbecue sauce.
Cook in the crock-pot 1 to 2 hours or in oven approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix oil, dill weed, garlic and Hidden Valley mix and pour over crackers.
Put in a paper bag and shake well.
Lay aside in bag and shake once in awhile to coat each cracker.
Store in Tupperware bowl or plastic bag to keep crisp or bake in oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Brown meat; drain and add sauce.
Split can of biscuits and line muffin pan with the biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add 1 tablespoon meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash the peppers and cut off the top with the stem.
Reserve the tops.
Scoop out and discard the seeds.
In an electric blender, blend onion, garlic and egg.
Add to meat.
Add rice, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Pour 2 tablespoons of water in each pepper and fill with meat.
Replace the tops and put upright into casserole.
Quarter tomatoes and add to casserole with 2 cups of water.
Sprinkle with dill and sugar.
Season and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until the rice is cooked.
Serves 6.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in sugar; add flour and mix.
Fold in whipped heavy cream.
Cook in a greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: strufoli
directions: Beat together eggs and salt.
Mix together flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Work dough a little to form a ball. Place dough under a bowl and let stand 2 hours or more.

title: easy crab meat dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine all ingredients.
Bake in low (300°) oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve as dip with crackers or fresh veggies.

title: cranberry chicken(so easy, so good!)
directions: Sprinkle the chicken breasts with salt and pepper and pound to flatten.
Heat the oil and butter in a skillet and add the chicken breasts and saute until lightly brown (about 5 minutes).

title: fried texas potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, green peppers, parsley, salt and pepper well.
Melt butter in heavy skillet until very hot.
Add potato mixture and fry at medium-high heat until brown.
Turn with spatula occasionally during frying.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate peanut pudding sundae
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, butter and peanuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In a large roaster, coat meat with flour and brown in shortening.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
If using a roast, shred meat and return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: bagels
directions: Melt the margarine in the scalded milk.
Proof the yeast with a pinch of sugar in the warm water.
Combine the two liquid mixtures and gradually blend in the flour and the salt until a soft, sticky dough is formed.
(A food processor is fine to start this.)
Knead well and place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Preheat the oven to 400°.
Boil about 3 quarts water with 2 tablespoons kosher salt.

title: broiled crab cakes
directions: Remove the crusts from the bread and crumble.
Mix the bread with the salt, pepper, parsley and celery flakes.
Beat the egg with the mustard.
Add crab meat and mix gently.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Shape into 6 balls, flatten slightly and put a pat of butter on top of each ball.
Broil on low oven rack approximately 20 minutes.

title: lena's pie
directions: Mix soft margarine, beaten eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla together.
Stir in chocolate or butterscotch chips.
Add nuts. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sour cream meat pie
directions: Brown meat in shortening. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion and tomato sauce, simmering 10 minutes. Cook noodles as directed and drain well. Blend cream cheese into meat mixture and fold in sour cream and noodles.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with cheese and bake.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until soft. Drain. Mix well all other ingredients. Pour into a baking dish. Sprinkle pepper on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: summer spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pasta and stir well.
Add olive oil to cover all real well.
Let sit all day or just before you cook pasta.
Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain pasta and add sauce; stir and serve.
Great cold the next day too!

title: cheese potato puffs
directions: Melt oleo
in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once, stirring
constantly for 2 minutes, until mixture leaves side of pan.
Remove.
Blend
in
egg
at a time.
Blend in cheese and potatoes.
Fry
in	oil
until brown on each side. Drain.
Serve hot.

title: baked ham
directions: Scrub ham well.
Soak overnight in water to cover.
If large ham soak 3 to 4 days with water changed each day.
Place ham in large pan that will allow cold water to cover ham.
Add brown sugar and vinegar to water.
Cover and simmer slowly 20 minutes to each pound of ham or until tender.
Do not boil; keep at simmering.
Let ham stand in stock several hours or overnight.
Remove from liquid. Mix brown sugar and bread crumbs together and put on top of ham. Brown at 375° to 400° until crust forms over top.

title: cabbage and potatoes
directions: In a microwave dish put a layer of chopped cabbage, layer of sliced potatoes, layer of chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with garlic salt (optional).
Then place another layer of cabbage, potatoes and onion; salt and pepper.
Put margarine and water on top.
Cover and cook in microwave 15 minutes on High.

title: homemade buttercream frosting
directions: Mix sugar and salt in small bowl. Add butter and milk.
Don't stir.
Microwave on low for 1 1/2 minutes or until batter is soft. Stir in vanilla. Beat on high speed of mixer until smooth.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Cream all ingredients, except pecans, together, mixing well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: apple coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs. Beat in vanilla, mix well. Add flour, soda, powder and salt. Fold in apples, coconut and nuts. Bake in 9x13 greased and floured pan at 350 degrees for 55 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery; remove from stove.
In another bowl mix in onion, celery, sage, salt and bread.
Add 2 beaten eggs. Add enough water to keep from being dry.
Lightly stuff chicken. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: granddaddy's banana cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter, then add 2 eggs and mix; make it creamy. Mash bananas and add to butter mixture. Add sour cream and baking soda separately and mix until foamy; add to butter mixture. Add flour into mixture and stir until blended. Mix in chopped walnuts (optional). Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (recommend Pyrex) at 350° for 30 minutes (may need more time; watch until golden brown).

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, cottage cheese and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on cookie sheet or 9
x 13 inch dish.
Spread Picante sauce on cheese mixture.
On top of this layer onion, taco cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Serve with nachos.
Best served at room temperature.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; cut each slice in half.
Put half the bread slices in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with shredded ham and cheeses.
Top with remaining bread slices.

title: jamie's pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, cloves and allspice) in a large bowl.
Add applesauce, water, shortening, eggs, raisins and chopped nuts and mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely.
Remove from pan to serving dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pat out crescent rolls into greased 7 x 12 casserole dish. Mash perforations together. Beat together eggs and milk with a little salt and pepper. Pour egg and milk mixture onto rolls; add bacon bits and mushrooms. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is not runny.

title: impossible ham and cheese pie
directions: Sprinkle
ham,	cheese and onion in 10-inch greased pie plate. Beat
remaining
ingredients
seconds	on high, in blender. Pour
into	plate.	Bake
at 375° until golden brown and knife inserted
in
center
comes out clean, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meatless taco salad
directions: Shred or cut lettuce in large bowl. Add diced tomatoes, sliced onions, beans, cheese and crushed Doritos. Right before serving, add whole bottle of Catalina salad dressing. Stir until salad is well covered with dressing.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix meat with taco seasoning mix. Simmer until done; drain and cool. Combine with remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Serve with taco chips.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl on medium speed; mix thoroughly.
Add flour, a little at a time, mixing constantly.
Add baking powder, milk, salt and extract. Beat thoroughly.
Fold in black walnuts.
Pour in a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in tube pan 10 minutes; invert on wire rack to cool.
No frosting needed. Serve with black walnut ice cream.

title: salem cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Roll into 1 large or numerous small balls.
These can be rolled into minced pecans, parsley or finely chopped, dried beef.
Chill before serving.

title: oriental steak
directions: Brown beef in olive oil and add garlic and cook until garlic turns yellow.
Add salt, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Cook 1/2 hour covered.
Add vegetables and consomme; cover and cook 5 minutes at high heat.
Stir in cornstarch and sugar, mixed with a little water to thicken slightly.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: hearty beef 'n cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans, cumin seed, garlic salt and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles; place in ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Press on bottom and sides.
Combine egg and 1 cup cheese; spread over crust.
Spread meat mixture onto crust.
Sprinkle rest of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stand for 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cherry triffle
directions: Line bottom of 3 1/2 qt. triffle bowl with cake, brush with liqueur.
Top with 1 c. filling, 1 c. pudding, repeat layers 3 times and chill for 3 hours.
Top with cream and optional almonds.

title: sherry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and add fruit slices.
For a group of 30 to 40 people, six times the recipe!

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat butter and egg until well mixed. Gradually beat in juice concentrate.
In large bowl, place flour, salt, baking powder, oats, walnuts and raisins.
Stir well.
Mix dry ingredients and creamed mixture together.
Drop by large teaspoons 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread or forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove lid from peanut butter and place whole jar in pan of hot water so it will be easy to spread.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Prepare the pastry and line pie tin.
Peel and cut the apples into eighths.
Mix 1/2 cup of the sugar with the cinnamon and mix with apples; spread into pastry.
Sift remaining 1/2 cup sugar with the flour.
Work the butter or margarine into this mixture until crumbly and spread over the apples.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes.
This recipe is also equally delicious prepared with fresh peaches when in season.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Salt and fry pork
chops.
Set	aside.	Place
rice
in baking dish.
Add	consomme
soup, bell peppers, onions, water and celery.
Stir to mix.
Lay	pork
chops
on
top and cover dish. Bake at 400° for
35 minutes or until rice is flaky and tender.

title: freezer dinner rolls
directions: Combine 2 c. flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large mixing bowl, stir mixture and set aside.

title: grace's onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in large glass bowl in microwave.
Add onions and saute for 12 to 15 minutes on High or until clear.
Place 1/2 cooked onions in a large pot.
Add seasonings, beef stock and water (reserve one can of water for next step.)
Use reserved can of water to puree second half of cooked onions.
Add this to onions on stove.
Bring to slow boil and simmer for about one hour.
(Can be microwaved completely in about 15 to 20 minutes on High.) Still recommend you puree one half of the onions, makes for a thicker soup.
Can be served in deep soup cup, floating an English muffin with Monterey Jack cheese.

title: gelatin lime salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Mix in hot gelatin one package of cream cheese until cheese is melted.
Add the pineapple, walnuts and celery.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rice lasagna
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; cool slightly.
Add egg whites and 1/3 cup Parmesan to rice; mix well.
Set aside. Combine Mozzarella, Ricotta and remaining Parmesan.
Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and oregano.
Layer in 3-quart casserole; top with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broiled shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp, but leave shell on.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Place on broiler pan and place closest to heat.
Broil for 3 minutes.
Baste and turn; broil for 2 minutes more.
Can be grilled 5 to 10 minutes, turning often.

title: roasted scottish pheasants(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: To prepare:
In small heatproof bowl, cover apricots with boiling water and soak 10 minutes.
Drain apricots and cut into quarters.
In a small sauce pan, simmer wine, liqueur, lime juice and sugar for 5 minutes.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into hot oil until golden brown.
Makes about 20 pieces.
Serve with honey.

title: scott's shrimp spaghetti
directions: In deep, heavy pot, saute onion and peppers in oil.
Add special tomato sauce and Ro-Tel.
Stir well.
Add roux and water. Cook on medium heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and salt and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add cooked (lightly salted) spaghetti to sauce.
Mix well.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let sit for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with fried bread.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes on top oven rack. Remove from oven and let cool. Mix mayonnaise, dressing mix, and cream cheese together thoroughly. Spread on top of roll crust. Top with vegetables. Refrigerate until ready to cut and serve.

title: vegetable soup *
directions: Combine all ingredients (except lentils, pasta and dill) in a soup pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and gently simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Add the lentils and pasta and continue simmering until they are cooked.
Stir in fresh dill just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dressing
directions: *You can use beef and broth, if you want, instead of chicken.

title: french toast
directions: Mix the egg substitute, milk and flavoring in a bowl and dip in the bread to soak up the mixture.
Grill on a griddle sprayed with Pam.
Serve with syrup, a fruit mixture or for something different, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, cream and chocolate together, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Increase heat, but do not stir again.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add butter and cool.
Add vanilla and nuts, beating until thick and heavy.
Turn into buttered pans.
Cut into squares.

title: tapponaide
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix and mash well.
Serve with veggies or chips.

title: sweet and sour sausages
directions: Cook slowly until done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare unbaked pie crust with your choice of decorative edge. Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites just until soft peaks form.
In large bowl with same beaters and with mixer at low speed, beat together egg yolks, pumpkin and next 7 ingredients until well blended.
With wire whisk or rubber spatula, gently fold beaten egg whites into pumpkin mixture.
Pour filling into crust and bake 45 minutes until filling is set.

title: peanut and ham dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container; blend until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with bite size portions of fresh cauliflower, tomatoes, green and red bell peppers, celery and carrot sticks.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: You need flour tortillas.
Make a hole in the middle and deep fat fry until golden brown on each side.
Drain and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add extracts to milk. Add baking powder to flour.
Alternate liquid and dry ingredients. Stir in the chopped walnuts. Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: white chili
directions: In crock pot, combine the beans, chicken, onion, sweet pepper, jalapeno peppers, garlic, cumin, salt and oregano.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cover and cook o low-heat setting for 8 to 10 hours on high setting for 4 to 5 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
May freeze.

title: zucchini tomato casserole
directions: Saute bread crumbs in butter and garlic.
In a 2-quart casserole, place a layer of tomato.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and brown sugar.
Add a layer of onion, layer of zucchini, bread crumbs and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, approximately.

title: shrimp shish kabob
directions: Wrap shrimp up in bacon and put barbecue sauce on them. Secure with toothpick in the middle of it so it doesn't fall apart.
Finally, put on the grill and cook until bacon is cooked.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach.
Remove stems and tear into pieces.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Heat wok or skillet.
Add oil.
Stir-fry mushrooms 1 minute.
Add spinach and garlic.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Toss with sesame seeds and crumbled bacon.
Serves 4!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Heat butter, sugar, milk and cocoa to a boiling.
Keep stirring.
Boil 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Add oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by spoonful on foil or waxed paper.
Refrigerate.

title: taco tossed salad
directions: Cook and stir ground
beef over medium heat until light brown. Drain.
Stir in
taco
sauce
and heat.
Toss lettuce, green peppers, tomatoes, olives, cheese, and chips.
Pour over hot beef mixture and
salad
dressing
over
lettuce and toss. Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
While noodles are cooking, combine soup and milk; mix well.
Add pepper and drained tuna to soup mixture. Add cubed Velveeta on top.
Drain noodles; add on top of other ingredients and mix well.
After mixed, top with Durkee onions. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes in an 11 x 7-inch casserole dish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, one at at time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Then add to butter mixture, starting and ending with flour alternately with milk.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place butter in shallow baking dish.
Melt in oven.
Combine cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper; set aside. Blend egg and milk in a shallow bowl.
Coat chops in crumb mixture; dip in egg mixture and again in crumb mix.
Place in dish with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Carefully turn chops and bake an additional 30 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake and dry out pork chops.

title: play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt, oil and alum.
Add the boiling water and stir until a ball forms.
Add food coloring of choice and work into dough.
Store in plastic bags in refrigerator.
Can be doubled!

title: turnip casserole
directions: Peel and slice turnips.
Parboil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and add onion, carrots and peas.
In a saucepan, melt butter; add flour.
Put in milk, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour over first 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream  cheese pound cake
directions: Combine butter, margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well. Add salt and vanilla, then one egg at a time, until blended well. Add flour and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coffee punch
directions: Whip whipping cream as normal.
Combine all other ingredients in chilled punch bowl.
Add whipping cream last.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add ginger ale, slowly.
Chill until slightly thickened and add nuts, celery and peaches.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef with onions; drain. Put in large pot and then add remaining ingredients. Simmer 2 hours.

title: pound cake cookies(very good)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and egg yolks alternately. Add vanilla.
I spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop dough by teaspoon (level full).
Leave some space between cookies.
They do spread.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from cookie sheet; place on cooling rack.
I find dough works better after cooling in refrigerator.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla flavoring.
Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda together.
Mix together 2 mixtures and add chocolate and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make golf ball size cookies; space balls 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix together and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
In mixing ingredients, soda should be dissolved in boiling water.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Mix together all the prepared vegetables.
Put chicken and oil in thick skillet or wok.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally until chicken is 3/4 done.
Add water, soy sauce and vegetables.
Reduce to low heat; cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in water; add while stirring constantly. Cook for 2 minutes and season with Lawry's seasoned salt and garlic powder.

title: ground turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour barbecue sauce on meat 15 minutes before done.
Serve hot.

title: cherry angel food trifle
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until blended.
Reserve 4 tablespoons Cool Whip.
Fold remaining Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour over cake cubes.
Mix well.
Spoon cake mixture into a pretty glass or bowl.
Spread cherry pie filling evenly over the top (or, if desired, layer half the cake mixture and cherry pie filling, repeating layers).
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with reserved whipped topping.

title: ceviche
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least overnight.
Add coconut cream on top before serving. (Ceviche lasts up to a week.)

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix water, rice, tomatoes, cheese and 1 teaspoon of Italian seasoning.
Pour in greased casserole.
Layer chicken on top. Sprinkle with remaining Italian seasoning and Parmesan cheese. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: winter squash quiche
directions: Brown bacon and drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Sprinkle cheese, bacon and onion in the warm pastry shell.
In a bowl, combine the eggs, milk, squash, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Garnish with bacon crumbs.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cut up broccoli that has been cooked and drained.
Mix together eggs, cheese, onion, half and half, and spices.
Place broccoli in pie crust.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts with champagne sauce
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Add chicken and brown.
Remove chicken to a 1-quart baking dish, reserving drippings in skillet. Add mushrooms to skillet and saute.
Remove mushrooms and set aside.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and save 1 cup juice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish sprayed with Pam.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on top.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Place cubed bread into 8-inch square buttered baking dish. Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour milk mixture and cheese over bread.
Let stand for 20 minutes or longer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve piping hot.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: chilled watermelon salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in a medium heat proof bowl. Stir until gelatin is dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add cold water and mix well.
Chill until partially set, about 55 minutes.
Add watermelon, undrained pineapple and 1 cup pecans to gelatin mixture and mix well.
Spoon into a salad bowl.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Place cream cheese in a medium bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer set at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add milk and sugar to cream cheese and beat until the mixture is smooth.
Fold whipped topping into cream cheese mixture.
Spread evenly over gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Chill until serving time.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together hash brown potatoes, cream of chicken, Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper, sour cream and onion.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt
butter; mix with crushed corn flakes.
Put mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 1 hour. Roll into small balls and dip into melted chocolate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter.
Place half of the mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Beat 2 cups of cold milk and vanilla pudding.
When set, pour over sugar and peanut butter mixture. When set up, beat 1/2 cup of cold milk and Dream Whip. Spread on top of pudding.
Add remaining sugar and peanut butter mixture to top.
Refrigerate.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening with sugar and hot water.
Cool.
Combine well beaten egg with yeast and add 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add shortening mixture to egg mixture and stir in flour.
Beat well and let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out dough and grease pan.
Let rise in warm place about 3 hours.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Pour celery soup and chicken broth over chicken.
Mix Bisquick and milk and pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and pour over Bisquick mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grace's own jam cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add soda and buttermilk.
Mix well. Stir in flour slowly.
Add spices, jam, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost with your favorite Caramel Icing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice together well.
Add 3/4 cup melted oleo.
Mix up stuffing mix according to box directions.
Cut up chicken.
Alternate layers of chicken, broccoli and stuffing mix with soup mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with 1 cup bread crumbs mixed with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or 1 hour if cold.

title: golden broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and pimento.
Stir into broccoli.
Top with crushed crackers. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: festive cherryettes
directions: Mix a soft dough.
Take 1 teaspoon of dough and form a ball. Press flat.
Place 1/4 to 1/2 cherry on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Double recipe:
30 small cookies.
Very good and rich!

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Look all the likely candidates for slaughter over carefully.

title: chinese fried nuts
directions: In large saucepan, over high heat, heat water to boiling.
Add nuts and bring back to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Rinse nuts under hot water.
Drain.

title: angel delight
directions: Cut pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Mix with marshmallows. Mix 3 tablespoons pineapple juice with mayonnaise.

title: fresh brisket
directions: Pour on liquids, salt and pepper and seasoning salt; turn and do the same to other side.
Cover with foil tightly.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours or until tender.

title: coney sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot dogs with chopped onions and mustard. Recipe may be doubled.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook, rinse and drain macaroni.
Mix milk and vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator or for 4 hours.

title: cheese and broccoli bake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add rice, broccoli, soup, onion and cheese. Cook in casserole at 350° one hour or until rice is done.

title: my favorite chili
directions: Brown beef; drain.
In Dutch oven, combine meat, ketchup, water, chili powder, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add partially drained beans. Simmer 15 minutes longer.
If desired, serve with topping of grated cheese.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan, simmering for 2 to 3 minutes. Season chicken, roll in flour and brown on both sides.
Bake in moderate oven, covered, for 45 minutes, basting frequently with sauce.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce. Using a 2-quart casserole dish which has a cover, alternate layers of buttered tortillas, meat sauce, olives and cheese.
Add water to cover.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut into pie-shaped wedges and serve.
Serves 6.
Kids love it!

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Put jello, pudding mix and water in a pot.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Stir often or it will scorch.
Pour into a bowl and add Dream Whip.
Mix together.
Add strawberries.
Refrigerate until set.
Can use other combinations of fruit and jello.
Works well in a mold.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put crushed pineapple, then cherry pie filling, dry cake mix, margarine, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: fried cod tongues
directions: Carefully wash fresh tongues and dry in a paper towel.
Allow 7 or 8 per person.
Put flour, salt and pepper together in plastic bag.
Put tongues in and shake them until evenly floured.
Cut up salt pork and fry until golden brown.
Remove pork cubes and fry tongues until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with mashed potatoes and green peas.

title: delicious corn bread
directions: Beat together egg, buttermilk and honey.
Mix well together all dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients, including melted butter and mix well.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square pan and bake.
Serve hot with butter and a chunk of Cheddar cheese.

title: candy kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on brown paper lined in bottom of pan.
Bake at 225° for 40 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix crushed crackers with margarine, onion and mushrooms.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of greased casserole pan.
Put layer of seafood on this.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Add enough milk to moisten just before baking.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until slightly brown on top.
May be made day before and baked just before serving.

title: cassidy's casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add spices and the tomato sauce.
Boil macaroni. Drain and add to meat. Top with cheese and let melt. Even tastier the next day. Serve with garlic toast and salad.

title: snack sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolk, cinnamon, salt, Adam's Best vanilla, Adams butter flavoring and Adams orange extract.
Gradually mix in flour.
Grease jelly roll pan (10 x 13-inch).
Spread dough 1/4-inch thick over pan. Spread egg white over dough.
Press chopped nuts into dough.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cut into strips approximately 1-inch wide and 4 inches long.
Using a narrow spatula, carefully remove each strip from pan while still warm.
Yield: about 30.

title: piccatina di vitella
directions: Dust each veal scaloppine lightly with flour and bread crumbs. Heat oil in large pan.
In a single layer, saute veal quickly on both sides.
Remove to platter.
Melt butter in the pan over low heat.

Return scaloppine and cook for 5 minutes. Season with salt, pepper and dry mustard. Add wine, cooking until it evaporates, about 4 minutes. Add lemon juice, capers, sage and parsley; sprinkle with grated cheese. Cook another 5 minutes. Serve each portion with remaining juices drizzled on top.

title: easy cheese tarts
directions: You will need cupcake liners.

title: easy crispy potato chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes in a bowl of ice water. Let stand 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine mustard and garlic. Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Spread mustard mixture on meaty side of chicken.
Place bone-side down on foil-lined pan.
Drain potatoes. Pat dry with a paper towel.
In a bowl, toss potatoes with olive oil, mixing well.
Spread about 1/3 cup potato shreds evenly over each breast to form a "skin".
Sprinkle lightly with pepper.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until the chicken is no longer pink inside and potato is golden.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix in Miracle Whip until moist.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: possum delight
directions: Preparation Time : Could take days.

title: rolls
directions: Combine yeast and teaspoon of sugar in a cup.
Add warm water. Stir until dissolved.
Set aside.
Put shortening in a large plastic bowl that will fit in microwave.
Microwave for approximately 1 minute to melt shortening.
Add salt and sugar. Microwave milk 1 to 2 minutes and add to shortening mixture.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Begin stirring in flour, 1 to 2 cups at the time. Continue until dough is no longer sticky but is still soft. Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight or until needed.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to boil.
Place remaining ingredients in blender.
While blending these ingredients, slowly add in sugar/vinegar mixture through top.
Blend until smooth and mixed well.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until meat starts to separate from bones. Remove breasts from stock.
Separate meat from bones; cut meat into 1-inch squares.
Spread meat over casserole dish.
Sprinkle broccoli over chicken.
Sprinkle dried beef over broccoli.
Mix can of chicken broth with cream of chicken soup and pour over broccoli.
Put pepper (bell) over top.
Mix dressing with chicken broth to moisten.
Spread over casserole; bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes, until dressing browns.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, brown onion until tender.
Remove from skillet and brown hamburger until done.
Stir in cooked onion, flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: crisco frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat with mixer on high until smooth and spreadable.

title: famous cabin monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Dip pieces into sugar mix.
Put pieces into greased angel food or Bundt pan.
Melt brown sugar and margarine.
Do not boil.
Pour over pieces in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: monster cheese dip
directions: Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place apple slices in the pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed well and pour into 2 baked graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk with handbeater until smooth.
Pour over broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix and margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Must be a full rolling boil and continue to boil for 4 minutes over medium heat and stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: mildred's cucumber pickle
directions: Slice cucumbers and pack tightly in gallon jug.
Mix first four ingredients with enough vinegar to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 4 to 6 weeks. Drain brine off good and put 5 pounds of sugar over cucumbers in jug.
Let stand.
Keep shaking and turning jug until sugar melts.
Will pull enough vinegar out of cucumbers to cover them.
Chill and enjoy.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer dish with vanilla wafers and bananas; repeat until dish is full.
Beat egg yolks until smooth.
Add sugar and flour.
Add milk and water.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Let cool.
Pour over bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: aunt katie's pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together 5 or 6 times.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture and mix well.
If batter appears to be a little stiff, add a little cold water.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: dreamy orange pie
directions: Mix crumbs and marmalade.
Put crumbs in 9-inch pie plate. Combine sherbet and frozen yogurt.
Pour over crumb crust.
Top with berries and keep frozen.

title: glazed ham
directions: Slice diagonally both ways lightly on top of ham.
Put in roasting pan; sprinkle with cinnamon and ground cloves and cover with 1 cup water.
Seal and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Mix the rest of ingredients in saucepan (not including pineapple, include only juice from pineapple) and bring to boil.
Pour over ham and re-seal with foil.
Continue to cook 45 more minutes at 350°. Cool for a few minutes and slice.
Place pineapple on top and serve.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Sift flour. Add 1 cup sugar and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into melted butter. Top with fruit. Sprinkle with remaining sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve hot with whipped topping or ice cream. (Best if baking dish is glass at 325°.)

title: hot pineapple punch
directions: Rinse lemon and lime.
Peel.
With a very sharp knife, remove the white membrane.
Squeeze juice.
Cut peel into very thin strips.
Place peel, honey and nutmeg in a big punch bowl.
Add lemon and lime juices.
Heat the pineapple juice.
Pour the hot pineapple juice over peel and spices.
Stir to dissolve.
Garnish and serve immediately.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate miracle whip cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add water,
miracle whip, and vanilla to dry ingredients. Stir until smooth. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in salt water until tender but not mushy.
Put in casserole.
In a small bowl put peanut butter and water; smash with a fork until smooth and creamy.
Add more water to keep smooth.
Pour over potatoes as a gravy.
You need enough to be level with potatoes in the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave about 5 minutes on High.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together; top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken with rice casserole
directions: Combine contents of box of rice and water in 2 1/2 quart casserole, salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Arrange on top of rice mixture.
Bake covered 1 1/4 hours at 375°.
Saute almonds in margarine.
Combine soup and milk.
When casserole is done, pour soup and milk mixture over it.
Put almonds on top and return to oven uncovered for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour together.
Then add 2 well beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips, pecans, vanilla and coconut.
Stir together.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
(Use deep dish pie crust because this may boil over.)

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Scald
milk,
stir
in
sugar, salt and butter, cool to lukewarm.
Combine
water and yeast in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat in milk mixture and egg.
Add half the flour, beat
until
smooth.
Stir
in
remaining
flour to make stiff batter.
Cover
tightly and refrigerate dough at least 4 hours or overnight.
Good for kolaches or pigs in blanket.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon honey chicken
directions: Brush chicken with melted butter, then coat with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Put skin side up in lightly oiled baking pan.
Pour other ingredients (well mixed) over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more until done.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook beef and drain. Crumble beef into slow cooker. Add pepper, basil, oregano, seasoned salt and dry soup mix. Stir in water, tomato sauce and soy sauce.

Then add celery and carrots. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Turn control to high. Add cooked macaroni and Parmesan cheese. Cover and cook on high 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley just before serving. Serve hot.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers).
Pour over crackers and mix well.

title: spinach and noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and put back into hot pan. Add sour cream, butter, spinach and pepper.
Toss mixture together.
Serve hot.
Can be used as main dish or side dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken; mix chicken and soup (no water) and sour cream.
Pour into baking dish.
Mash Ritz and spread over top.
Melt oleo and spoon over Ritz.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350°
for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Put yeast in bowl in 1/2 cup of lukewarm water.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat oil to 350°, 3-inches deep.
Mix dry ingredients. Combine eggs, milk and butter; mix together with dry ingredients. Add corn and stir to combine.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Deep fry about 5 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve warm.

title: ham and cheese rollups
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, and margarine.
Spread on ham slices.
Roll up the short sides.
Chill and then cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Spread in pie shell.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Mix white sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl.
Add biscuits and shake to coat dough with cinnamon sugar.
Put
biscuits
in	tube pan sprayed with Pam. Pour over
biscuits
the
brown
sugar, margarine and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn out onto plate.

title: fresh peach crunch
directions: Mix together peaches, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and milk. Put in 8 x 8-inch glass pan.
Now make topping of 1 cup sugar, butter, 1 cup flour, egg and baking powder.
Put on top of peaches and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish in order given. Save enough Velveeta cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend ingredients well.
Pour batter in greased pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Make 9-inch cake.

title: chess pie (2)
directions: Mix sugar and meal and add 1 egg at a time, until 5 eggs have been added.
Add margarine, milk, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cooper carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Boil until tender; drain.
Mix oil, soup, vinegar, sugar, mustard, onion, bell pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add carrots and refrigerate overnight. Warm before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Fill crust with sliced apples; sprinkle sugar, pieces of butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Roll upper crust, moisten edge of lower crust on pan.
Cover with pie dough.
Cut openings for steam to escape.
Press edges together with fork or fingers.
Brush top of pie with milk or egg white.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes with foil covering crust at edge only.
Uncover.
Bake about 20 minutes or more, until browned.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Boil noodles.
Add cooked noodles to saute mix in large pan.
Set aside.
Mix soup, Velveeta and Milnot over medium heat.
Stir constantly; do not let it burn. Add to noodle mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered. Then uncover and place sliced Velveeta cheese over top.
Bake for 15 minutes more.
Let sit for 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Salt hen and cook.
Remove from broth and cut in small pieces. Cook onion, celery and bell pepper in 1 cup of broth until tender.
Cook noodles.
Warm soup.
Add chicken, onion, celery and bell pepper
mix.
In a 1-quart casserole dish, use alternate layers of noodles and chicken.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 25 minutes.

title: candied spiced walnuts
directions: Preheat oven at
300°.	Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat egg
white,
gradually adding sugar and salt until stiff. Fold in nuts.
Add spices and cover over nuts.
Spread mixture in buttered pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, turning several times until nuts are lightly browned and crisp.	Cool in pan on wire rack for a	few minutes.
Turn
out
on
paper towels to cool completely and dry. Store in airtight container.

title: ham stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand for 5 minutes or until leaves are limp.
Mix ham, rice, mayonnaise, egg, pickle, celery and onion.
Place 1/2 cup mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Fold leaves over filling, envelope fashion.
Roll and secure with toothpick or string.
Place in casserole.
Dot with butter and cover with chicken broth.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oreo cool cookie crumble
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Stir until ice cream is melted.
Fold in crumbled cookies.
Pour into individual dessert glasses or serving bowl. Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with a whole cookie at the side of dish.
If you're counting calories, try making this recipe with sugar-free Jell-O gelatin.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and salt in saucepan.
Put on low heat for 2 minutes.
Do not let sugar melt.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Increase heat and boil rapidly 1 minute stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
In a separate saucepan, add milk, flour and salt.
Place milk and flour mixture on a warm burner, stirring slowly until mixture thickens.
When mixture thickens, add cheese and stir.
Drain potatoes; add meat and pour cheese sauce (mixture) over potatoes; bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Eat.

title: pudding fruit salad
directions: Blend pudding with milk and orange juice until it thickens, add sour cream mix well. Stir in fruit, let set for 2 or 3 hours or over night.

title: chocolate nut caramels
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cream, butter, syrup and chocolate in large heavy saucepan.
Bring to gentle boil over low heat.
Cook, stirring frequently until mixture reaches firm-ball stage.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and pecan halves. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut in 1-inch squares; wrap in waxed paper.
Makes 64 caramels.

title: shortcake(for strawberries)
directions: Mix dry ingredients first (flour, salt and baking powder). Cut in Crisco.
Bake at 400° in greased pan about 25 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Start watching around 20 minutes.
Cool 10 to 12 minutes when done on cookie sheet.
This is done by mounding dough for individual servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together until light and fluffy. Add the eggs and vanilla flavoring and beat well.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together the eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan the bread, sausage (crumbled on top) and cheese (sprinkled on top).
Pour egg mixture over the above. Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Break up angel food cake into little pieces and put in bottom of bowl.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, powdered sugar and can of milk.
Spread over angel food cake.
Mix strawberries and glaze and spread over the top.
With a spoon punch holes in several places to allow the strawberry mixture to seep through.

title: luscious potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Moisten with salad dressing.
Put into bowl and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Add salt to egg whites and beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat until smooth and glossy.
Slowly add Karo syrup, beating until firmly peaked.
Fold in vanilla.
This is good topped with coconut.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Bake in casserole dish.

title: mrs. wade's divinity
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water.
Cook slowly until it forms a crystal in cold water.
Pour slowly into beaten egg whites.
Beat with mixer and then spoon until ready to drop on wax paper.
Pecans or coconut can be added just before it hardens.
It can also be colored with food coloring, if desired.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 minutes and cool.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Mix and add enough clean, white snow to create an ice cream texture.

title: diet carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburg, bacon and onion.
Mix brown sugar, white sugar, catsup, salt, dry mustard and vinegar.
Drain all beans, except pork and beans.
Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a loaf pan. Blend first 6 ingredients.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: no bake lemon cheesecake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water; cool.
In large mixer bowl, beat Milnot; set aside.
In small mixer bowl, cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello mixture.
Add slowly the cream mixture into whipped Milnot.
Pour into pan and sprinkle top with 1/2 cup saved crumbs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer broccoli (precooked in microwave for 6 minutes).
Cover with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with onion and Cheddar cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and spices.
Spread over crust.
Top with raw vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery, green pepper and sliced ripe olives).
Over this add grated cheese.
Refrigerate.
(Use a large cookie sheet.)

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt
margarine.
Mix
sugar,
peanut butter and margarine. Roll
into small balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin separately.
Combine
after melting.
Mix well. Dip balls into mixture and let dry on wax paper.

title: chili
directions: Kidney beans can be substituted for the pinto beans.

title: sauerbraten meat balls
directions: Mix beef, 1 teaspoon salt and diced onion.
Sprinkle bread with milk and taco seasoning; add to beef.
Shape into balls and fry in oleo.
Mix water and all other ingredients.
Pour over meat balls and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: dilled shrimp mousse pate
directions: Pour tomato juice into 2-quart pan.
Sprinkle in gelatin and let stand about 5 minutes.
Place over medium heat and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
To gelatin add lemon juice, salt, Worcestershire, sour cream, dill and all but 10 to 15 shrimp.
Place half the mixture in a blender and whirl until smooth.
Pour into a 2 1/2 cup mold. Repeat with remaining mix.
Cover and chill until 4 hours or until set.
Unmold onto serving plate and garnish with reserved shrimp, greens, olives and lemon wedges.
Serve with crackers.

title: grandma opal's rigatoni(anne reece's childhood favorite)
directions: In a large pot, combine meat, onion, celery and celery leaves, parsley, basil, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until meat is very tender and falling off the bone, about 1 hour.

title: mom's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until barely tender; drain well.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine mushrooms and French dressing with macaroni. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Drain off excess dressing.
Combine and add remaining ingredients; toss with macaroni.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Put layer of stuffing in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer chicken, can of chicken soup, can of water, layer of chicken, stuffing, mushroom soup, can of water, another layer of chicken and stuffing.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter; pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well in one bowl.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet sprayed lightly with "Pam."
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Blend in flour. Add other ingredients except shrimp and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer until tomatoes cook down, about 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook slowly 30 minutes or more.

title: cream of reuben soup
directions: Combine broths, celery, onion and green pepper; bring to a boil. Simmer until tender-crisp (5 minutes). Add cornstarch and water; cook until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in beef, cheese and kraut. Melt butter and stir in half and half. Add to other soup mix; heat through, but do not boil. Garnish with chives, if desired. Serves 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, cloves and allspice.
Add shortening, water, nuts, raisins and applesauce.
Beat 2 minutes in mixer on medium speed. Add egg and beat 2 minutes more.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Make brownies according to instructions.
Pour half of batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chili mix to meat and mix well. Add soup and beans and mix well.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue kabobs
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, sherry, sugar, mustard and garlic; add chicken.
Marinate meat 4 to 5 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Spray skewers with Pam; alternately thread chicken, tomatoes, peppers, onion and mushrooms; brush with marinade. Spray unheated grill rack with Pam.
Place kabobs on grill when coals are ready.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until done, turning occasionally.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches and mix with all other ingredients except the crust.
Pour all into the crust and cover with the second crust.
Vent and decorate as desired.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes and then lower temperature to 350° and bake another 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: three layer casserole
directions: Cook the vegetables in microwave.
Put vegetables in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Add beef. Top with mashed potatoes. Bake in a 350° oven until potatoes are golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken gourmet
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.
Spread rice over margarine.
Put chicken pieces in pan.
Add soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix it through.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add gelatin until dissolved.
Mix remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze for at least 24 hours. Two hours before serving, take out of freezer.
When ready to serve, break up with fork and add ginger ale.
Any gelatin can be used to change colors.

title: sue's six layer dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and set aside.
In a shallow casserole dish, layer in this order:
refried beans, sour cream mixture, tomatoes, onion, lettuce and cheese. Top with sliced black olives, if desired.
Chill and serve with nacho chips.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Beat margarine until fluffy.
Add vanilla flavoring to the sugar and beat well, then add the lemon flavoring and then the eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and blend well with creamed mixture and sour cream.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Heat up beans, then remove.
Heat 1 cup boiling water, soup mix and mushrooms.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour over beans and serve.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Parboil eggplant until tender.
Layer with remaining ingredients.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and mix with bread crumbs. Place on top of layered ingredients.
Bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, white sugar and vanilla together and toss grapes in mixture. Place in a 9 x 13 dish. Mix the brown sugar and pecans and sprinkle over grape dish.

title: bacon stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Grease skins of potatoes and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until soft to touch.
Cut a long oval slice from top of potato and scoop out pulp into a bowl.
Add butter, sour cream, egg, salt and sugar to potato pulp.
Beat well; stir in bacon. Place mixture back into potato shells, stuffing them high. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon; drain on paper towel and set aside.
Use 3 tablespoons of fat to saute onion, celery, bell pepper and bay leaf.
Cook until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Mix in flour, then corn, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until soup comes to a boil and is slightly thickened.
Just before serving, stir in 1 cup cheese. Spoon over soup 1/2 cup cheese and bacon pieces.

title: easier-than-a-mix chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar, water and vanilla until well blended. Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda. Add all at once to liquid ingredients; mix until just blended. Spread batter in 2 greased and floured 8-inch layer pans. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and oleo on low heat in large pan, stirring constantly, until melted.
Add the Crispix; stir until coated.
Put powdered sugar in brown paper bag.
Add coated cereal; shake well.
Store in cereal box in refrigerator.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, lime juice and salt.
Cook in double boiler until the mixture coats a spoon.
Remove from heat and add gelatin (which has been soaked in 1/2 cup cold water) and rind.
Mix well, chill; until the mixture begins to thicken. Beat egg whites with remaining sugar until they stand in soft peaks.
Fold into a 9-inch baked pie crust or a crumb crust. Chill.
Spread with real whipped cream just before serving.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Tear cake into small chunks.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water, no cold water.
Add partially thawed strawberries and juice.
Put in refrigerator until it begins to set.
Add Cool Whip to jello.
Pour over cake.
Chill.

title: kentucky chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, cornmeal and flour in large bowl.
Stir in eggs.
Blend in half and half, margarine, vanilla and salt; pour filling into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 375°; continue baking until puffed and golden, 45 to 50 minutes.
Let pie cool to room temperature before slicing and serving.

title: hummingbird cake(irene lucas' recipe)
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in almonds. Beat eggs slightly; combine with oil, almond extract, bananas and undrained pineapple. Add to dry ingredients; mix thoroughly, but do not beat. Spoon batter into a well oiled 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert on cake rack. Remove pan.
Cool thoroughly before frosting.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chili beans and vegetables
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat oil.
Add eggplant and saute for 10 minutes over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with flour and toss eggplant to coat.
Add onions, green pepper, garlic, stewed tomatoes, kidney beans, oregano, salt and water.
Carefully mix ingredients together.
Return to heat. Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover.
Lower heat and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Do not overcook because vegetables should be crisp.
Serve on fluffy cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: korean barbecue fish
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add to the fish and marinate at least 30 minutes. Can pan fry, broil or cook on the grill. Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine the jello with the boiling water.
Cool and thicken very slightly. Add the remaining ingredients.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Put in pie pan and cover with shredded lettuce and tomatoes, cut in small pieces.
Put sliced black olives on top. Serve with nacho chips.

title: party rolls
directions: Mix butter, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onion and poppy seed.
Split rolls and spread mixture on the bottom half of each roll. Top with thin slices of cheese and ham. Replace top halves of rolls. Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: beef and spinach
directions: Slice beef thinly.
Rinse spinach.
Heat oil in pan, when heated, stir-fry beef until redness is gone.
Mix in spinach until all leaves have shrunk.
Put in soy sauce and pepper for seasoning.
Then beef and spinach is ready to be served with rice or potatoes.

title: gluten free almond torte
directions: You can toast the almonds in a dry skillet or other pan in a 325° oven, stirring often, until color turns to tan.
Remove and cool.
Then put them in a food processor to grind.

title: apple cake(moist, fruity)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, spices, nuts and apples.
Add flour and baking soda; mix well.

title: peanut butter and chocolate cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin pans with 12 paper baking cups; place 1 tablespoon of graham cracker crumbs in each cup; set aside.
In small mixer bowl, beat both packages of cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat.
Beat in milk.
Add eggs; beat just until blended.
Divide mixture in half.
Add melted chocolate to one half and add peanut butter to the other half of cream cheese mixture.

title: yummy breakfast bake
directions: Unroll 1 can of crescent rolls into bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix cheese with 1 cup of sugar and vanilla; spread over rolls. Place 2nd can of rolls on top, same as the 1st. Pour melted margarine on top. Mix 1/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Let cool. Slice into squares.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix well and pack into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or shape into loaf in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: bacon tots
directions: Wrap Tater Tots with 1/2 strip of bacon while the Tater Tots are frozen, overlapping the bacon.
Place in oven for 30 to 45 minutes until brown at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: wild and tender
directions: Marinate beef 15 to 20 minutes in wine mixed with salt, garlic salt and pepper.
In baking dish add 1/4 inch of water, onions, celery,
carrots, broccoli, basil and oregano.
Cover with	foil and
steam	vegetables until tender.
Prepare rice following directions	on
package.
Grill
meat
to
desired doneness. After
meat
is
cooked,
cut
into
pieces.
On
a platter, arrange
bed
of
rice.
Place
meat
on rice and add steamed vegetables to the edge.
Cover vegetables with grated cheese while hot to insure melting.
Serves 2.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook and cool rice.
Add all ingredients and chill.
Amounts of ingredients may vary according to taste.

title: coconut ice
directions: Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Fold and place sheet of aluminum foil down middle of pan to divide it in half.
Heat sugar, cream of tartar and milk to boiling in heavy saucepan.
Let simmer until 230° on thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon half into one side of pan.
Blend in food coloring into remaining half and pour into other side of pan.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours. Cut into 1-inch cubes.
For gifts, alternate colors in apothecary jar.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In a saucepan, put milk and marshmallows.
Heat just enough to melt marshmallows.
Add crackers and work together with hands. Add rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased bunt pan and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a small bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon. Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll
1 1/2 cans of biscuits in mixture and place in Bundt pan. In a saucepan, melt one stick oleo and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add vanilla.
Pour half of this mixture over biscuits in pan.
Roll the remainder of biscuits in sugar-cinnamon mixture and place them in the pan.
Pour the rest of the butter mixture over the biscuits.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not cut, pull them apart.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Mix together Ricotta cheese, broccoli and eggs.
Spread on bottom crust.
Spoon chopped tomatoes on bottom crust.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Top with second crust. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
One-half cup of pizza sauce last few minutes of baking.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 cup Crisco and set aside.
Mix 1 cup very warm water with 3 packages yeast.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon baking powder.
Mix the two mixtures together.
Add 2 beaten eggs and 6 cups flour.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen rolls.
This can also be stored in the refrigerator if you don't want to use it all.

title: barbecue beans-hawaiian
directions: Mix ingredients to your taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked salmon fillet
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, shortening and pumpkin.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with water.
Stir in nuts and fruit.
Fill greased tin can 1/2 to 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange; add sugar.
Mix Jell-O in boiling water and let set until it begins to thicken.
Add celery, pecans, cranberries and orange (which has been prepared with sugar).
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in salt water until tender.
Take chicken off bone and mix with chicken soup and sour cream.
Melt butter. Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Put on top of chicken mixture and cook at 350° until bubbling hot and crust is brown.

title: rich hot chocolate
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Over medium heat, slowly add water.
Heat thoroughly.

title: bean salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together, refrigerate and serve cold. Good way to recycle leftover pinto beans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine and
refrigerate
overnight.
Put
in casserole and top with 1	cup
grated Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup crushed potato chips. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake in conventional oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Test with a fork.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in slow cooker on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: glazed peach pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients, place in unbaked pie shell. Bake 20 minutes in 425° oven.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: almond crunch
directions: Tips:
Make only 1 batch at a time.
Heavy saucepan is a must to prevent burning.

title: potato dauphinoe's
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy pan and slowly bring to a boil.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes and add to hot milk.
Add garlic and cream.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Place potatoes in a well-buttered casserole.
Bake in 325 degree oven until sauce has thickened.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese has melted.

title: old fashion corn bread dressing
directions: Combine crumbled cornbread with crumbled white bread or biscuits.
Soak dry mixture with chicken stock.
In a skillet, saute onion and celery.
Add to other mixture along with beaten eggs and sage.
Mix well and add enough of the liquid to make right consistency.
Bake in bread pan at 400° about 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in order in an 8 x 10-inch pan:
bean dip, avocado, sour cream, taco mix, lemon juice and mayo stirred together, tomatoes, green onions, olives and Cheddar cheese.

title: crab-topped potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes on High power for 12 minutes or cook potatoes in oven at 350° until soft.
(Potatoes will bake in a hurry if they are boiled in salted water for about 10 minutes before popping into a very hot oven.)

title: golden sausage nuggets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well. Cook over low heat until done, turning to brown on all sides. Drain on paper towels. Combine flour, salt, paprika and cheese. Cut in butter with pastry blender. Mix with hands until dough is smooth. Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each sausage ball, covering sausage completely. Place on greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Servings: 4 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix butter and stuffing mix in bowl.
