Cook squash and onion and then add cream of chicken, sour cream, carrots and cheese.
Line bottom of baking dish with 1/2 of stuffing mixture.
Spread squash mixture as middle layer and remainder of stuffing mixture on top. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: overnight chocolate yeast cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add melted chocolate, milk and yeast.
Mix.
Beat in flour and salt sifted together.
Fold in stiffly-beaten egg whites.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, add baking soda dissolved in hot water and vanilla; mix well.
Put in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, milk, flavoring, egg yolks (well beaten), flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites to a stiff froth.
Add to mixture.
Add enough more flour to roll.
Cut off a small piece of dough and roll on floured board.
Sprinkle with sugar and shape with cookie cutter.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters.
Steam cabbage until tender.
Wrap hamburger in cabbage leaves.
Cook in tomato juice in oven until done (about 1 hour).

title: swedish chicken
directions: Spread dried beef in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Wrap each chicken piece in a slice of bacon and place on top of dried beef.
Pour mixture of the soup and sour cream over top of chicken.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours. Uncover for several minutes before serving.

title: pear butter
directions: To prepare pulp, quarter and core pears.
Cook until soft. Add only enough water to prevent sticking.
Press through a sieve or food mill.
Measure pulp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick, about 35 minutes. As mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Cool.
Test for seal. Makes 4 pints.

title: party turnovers
directions: In skillet combine soup mix and meat.
Brown well.
Blend in cheese.
Separate rolls as per package directions, then cut in half.
Place spoonful of meat mixture in center of each triangle. Fold over and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 48 turnovers.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Break eggs into a cup measure.
Add 1/2 cup milk or more to make 1 cup.
Beat eggs and milk thoroughly.
Add liquid and parsley to the flour mixture and stir until smooth and stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls over steaming hot chicken soup or stew.
Cover.
Allow to steam over low heat for 10 minutes.
Do not lift cover.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Make lemon filling in medium size pan.
Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Gradually add water, stirring until smooth.
Over medium heat, bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute until shiny translucent. Quickly stir some of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Pour back into mixture and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, lemon zest and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Saute 1/2 pound ground beef.
Drain on an absorbent paper towel.
The next 3 ingredients are prepared and placed in separate mounds, ready to be used. Grease a large iron skillet.
Heat.
Sprinkle a very thin layer of meal in skillet and brown slightly.
Pour 1/2 batter in skillet. Sprinkle cheese, then meat, peppers and onion evenly over batter. Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mushroom steak and potatoes
directions: Cut steak into medium size pieces (3 x 5-inches).
Brown steak with diced onion, Worcestershire sauce, seasoning salt and pepper. (This should be done in a Dutch oven type pan as this dish is also baked.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 cup crushed cornflakes over casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over cornflakes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix Carnation milk, sugar and salt.
Put in pan over low heat; heat to boiling point.
Boil 5 minutes exactly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add diced marshmallows, peanut butter chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until smooth and ingredients are melted.
Spread on buttered platter.

title: amish cookies
directions: Combine sugars, oleo and oil; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill a while; drop small balls on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out just before turning brown.
Fruit, nuts or chocolate chips may be added to the batter.

title: belgian waffles
directions: In a medium size bowl, beat egg whites just until stiff, moist peaks form; set aside.
In large bowl, combine egg yolks, granulated sugar and salt.
Beat yolk mixture until thick.
Blend in milk, vanilla and the 4 tablespoons butter.
Continue beating while gradually adding flour; blend well.
Gently fold in beaten egg whites.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into a graham cracker crumb crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until center is set. Cool, then refrigerate for about 3 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put pineapple, then pie filling, dry cake mix, nuts and margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tangy vegetable dip
directions: Combine carrot, green pepper strips, onion and water in 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover and microwave at High (100%) until vegetables are tender-crisp, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once.
Set aside.
Place cottage cheese, yogurt and lemon juice in food processor or blender and process until smooth.
Place in small bowl and add cooked vegetables and dill weed.
Mix well.
Cover with plastic and chill.
Combine garlic powder, paprika and cayenne in small bowl.
Arrange vegetable spears on serving platter and sprinkle with spice mixture.
Serve vegetables with dip.
Yield: 12 servings, 36 calories per serving.

title: turkey roll ups
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on the box, place some stuffing on each slice of turkey, roll up, place in microwave dish, pour gravy over and put in for 5 to 7 minutes.
Or in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange candy slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add 1 cup buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add soda to remaining 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add to egg mixture.
Combine salt and flour.
Stir into egg mixture.
Stir in dates, orange slices and nuts. Blend well.
Line a tube pan with well-greased brown paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for 2 hours and 30 minutes.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Add one teaspoon salt to cabbage and let stand one hour. Squeeze out the water and add the carrots and peppers to cabbage while cabbage is standing.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs, cheese, milk and salt.
Place sausage on bread and then pour beaten egg mixture on top of the sausage.
Remaining cheese goes on top.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: millet-raisin pudding
directions: Soak 3/4
cup
dry
soy beans overnight.
Drain.
Blend beans with 2 cups hot water until creamy.
Combine in saucepan with other
ingredients
and
boil.
Turn to low and simmer 45 minutes. Bake in hot oven to lightly brown top.

title: deer chili
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until desired consistency.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender; drain.
Measure sweet potatoes in bowl and beat until smooth.
Mix dry ingredients. Stir in sweet potatoes.
Combine eggs, butter and milk, then mix with other ingredients.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: *crab imperial
directions: Blend all ingredients together with the fingers so that the lumps of crabmeat are not broken.
Heap mixture lightly into crab shells.
Top with a light coating of mayonnaise and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Work in flour and baking powder.
Roll out on floured surface. Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven until lightly browned.
tags: baking powder for each c. flour

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender. Drain, reserving liquid. Set vegetables aside. In same kettle, saute onions in margarine until soft. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thick. Stir in vegetables. Add 1 cup of reserved liquid. Add more liquid to make desired consistency.

title: strawberry bread with strawberry cream cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Make a well in center of flour mixture; pour strawberries, oil, egg white and pecans into well.
Mix until thoroughly combined.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onion and salt, let stand for 1 hour. Pour liquid off. Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed. Add squash and boil 20 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 4 hours before serving.
Garnish with fresh slices strawberries and topping.

title: linguini and scallops
directions: Combine scallops, lemon juice and parsley in dish; cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
In large frypan, cook onion and garlic in oil and 1/2 margarine until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes and seasoning; simmer 30 minutes.
Drain scallops.
Melt margarine in another frypan and stir scallops for about 2 minutes.
Stir in cream, nutmeg and tomatoes.
Serve over cooked, hot linguini. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar and egg; beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and fruit cocktail.
Cover with brown sugar and chocolate chips for the frosting.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nectarine quick cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Halve nectarines, pit and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside. Combine Bisquick, milk, 2 tablespoons granulated sugar, cooking oil and egg.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange nectarine slices in rows on top of batter. Pour melted butter over fruit.
Combine the 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over nectarines.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shirley's carrot bread
directions: Mix flour, sugars, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir together in another bowl carrots, oil, water, eggs and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients.
Stir well. Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except the nuts.
Mix with electric beater 3 minutes.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake one hour or until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken "n" rice
directions: Open soups; add, with water, into saucepan, and heat until blended.
Remove from heat.
Add rice and chicken; mix.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, pumpkin, eggs and oil, beating well.
Sift in gradually dry ingredients and mix well.
Use 1 pound loaf pans. Makes 3 loaves.
Line bottom of pans with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Put evaporated milk and marshmallows in double boiler and melt marshmallows.
Roll graham crackers very fine.
Mix cracker crumbs, raisins, nuts, cherries and pineapple in bowl and pour first mixture over them.
Mix well and form into a loaf.
Wrap in waxed paper and place in refrigerator.

title: brown sugar oatmeal bread
directions: Bring 2 cups water to boil.
Stir in oats and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat; add margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Add oat mixture and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes, by hand. Gradually add 2 more cups flour, mixing until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out and knead in remaining 1/2 cup of flour for about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise about 1 hour until doubled.
Butter 2 loaf pans and divide dough in half.
Roll each half onto a floured surface to a 12 x 18-inch rectangle.
Roll up from the narrow end; tuck ends under and place seam side down in prepared pans.
Brush with butter, if desired. Cover and let rise about 1 1/2 hours until sides come up to the top of the pans.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Cool on racks.

title: custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: In blender combine ingredients.
Blend 30 seconds.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. (Pie will rise but will settle as it cools to form light crust.)

title: cut glass
directions: Dissolve orange jello in 1 cup hot water with 1/2 cup cold water.
Do the same with the lime and cherry jello.
Set aside until firm.
Then cut into squares.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Soften cream cheese. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar; add liquid and mix real good.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell and refrigerate.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
(Do not beat.)
Mix lightly by hand. Fill greased iron skillet or muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn pone
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve as corn bread, cake or with milk in a bowl.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in bouillon.
Layer broccoli cuts, lima beans, whole onions and mushrooms.
Cover with soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 10.

title: fried okra
directions: Salt and pepper okra to taste.
Mix egg and milk.
Dip okra into mixture and dust lightly with flour or cracker meal.
Place floured or mealed okra on cookie sheet.
Heat oil (375°) to bubbling (important!) in skillet or electric frypan before adding okra.
Oil should cover okra.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain in colander or on paper towels.

title: dump salad
directions: In medium bowl, dump all ingredients.
Stir after each addition.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and flour, then stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in one 9-inch deep pie shell or 2 regular 9-inch shells.

title: baked crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving the paprika to sprinkle on the top.
Spread in a small baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top and bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers, vegetables, or crusty bread.

title: green and white salad
directions: Tear broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Combine vegetables in large bowl; combine remainder and mix well.
Pour over veggies and toss lightly to coat.
Cover and chill.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour ingredients over cucumbers.
Stir and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Will last up to 3 months and longer.
Makes a very light summer salad.

title: fried pastry
directions: Mix egg yolks and salt; beat 10 minutes.
Add sugar, egg white, vanilla and rum; beat.
Add flour; knead until dough blisters.
Roll paper thin on floured board; cut and bow.
Fry in deep fat until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: roz's cheesecake
directions: Grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl at high speed, beat cream cheese and cottage cheese until creamy.
Gradually beat in sugar and eggs.
At low speed, beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add butter and sour cream.
Beat just until smooth.

title: chili chicken
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
Saute onion in your 2 cups broth (saved) along with garlic to taste.
Add green chilies and soups (set aside).
Tear up tortillas (set aside).
Chop chicken and add to broth and soup mixture.
Pour half into casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of tortillas, then remainder of chicken and remainder of tortillas.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Finely chop the shrimp and place in a bowl.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 1-1/2 c.

title: fresh raspberry pie(can use strawberries if preferred)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add crushed berries and water.
Cook at slow boil until consistency thickens and becomes clear.
Cool.

title: mock caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix and pour over romaine or your favorite lettuce.
Add croutons and shredded Parmesan cheese.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into ungreased 9x13 pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix coconut, flour, sugar and salt all together in a large bowl.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Blend with blender or hand mixer, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix well, then put into 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: venison stew
directions: Shake beef in flour.
Add all ingredients to slow cooker. Cook on low for 6 hours.
Can also be shredded and used for hot sandwiches.

title: raw cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite-sized pieces; do not thaw peas.
Lightly toss all vegetables.
Mix dressing by stirring together Miracle Whip, sour cream or yogurt, sugar, garlic salt, seasoned salt, and pepper; pour over vegetables.
Let set in the refrigerator overnight to marinate.
Makes a lot!

title: chicken breasts positano
directions: Remove cores and seeds from tomatoes.
Dice tomato pulp and add to saucepan.
Discard rest of tomato and juice.
Add onion, garlic and oil to saucepan and stir.
Season with salt and pepper. Stir in lemon juice and sugar.
Let mixture stand, loosely covered, in a warm place, for several hours.

title: creamed ham and mushrooms
directions: Melt shortening, then add flour, salt and pepper and stir until smooth.
Add milk slowly, and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add ham, mushrooms with juice, onion and green pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve on biscuits, toast, rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to cooking directions.
Combine remaining ingredients with noodles.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done. Drain water. Combine all ingredients. Put in the refrigerator until cool.

title: canned tomatoes #1
directions: Peel tomatoes by putting in hot boiling water for about 3 minutes or skins
crack.
Place or stuff in clean sterilized jars and add salt.
Seal
with
jar
seals and place on cookie sheet in cold oven.
Turn
oven
to
250° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix melted shortening with brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Use large pan, 11 x 17-inch.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, dry soup mix, water chestnuts and onions.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Can serve in hollowed out pumpernickel round loaf with bread pieces or with crackers or cut up assorted vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lillian hellman's pot roast
directions: Choose the beef you prefer.
Place in a heavy pan.
Smother the beef with all remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours with a cover or foil.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine potatoes, water, onion, celery and bouillon.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash potatoes slightly; do not drain.

title: beefsteak tomato and asparagus salad
directions: *Available at cheese shops and some specialty food stores. Regular Mozzarella can be substituted.

title: barb's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together with mixer the peanut butter, brown sugar and Crisco until light and fluffy.
Add milk, vanilla and egg.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Stir in chips and raisins.
Drop dough onto pans lined with parchment paper.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: jiffy dessert cake
directions: Mix Jiffy (one layer) cake according to package directions. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 15 minutes only (until lightly brown).
Cool in pan.
Prepare lemon or other flavor instant pudding mix according to package directions.
Pour over cold cake.
Let pudding set until firm.
Spread the Cool Whip or package of prepared Dream Whip over pudding. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: spinach supreme frittata
directions: In a large skillet cook onions in butter until tender but not brown.
Add spinach and garlic.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add cooked rice and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir into rice mixture. Turn into well buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate-mint dessert spread
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and slowly cook until thickened.
Stir constantly to avoid scorching.
Cool pudding mixture completely.
In glass serving bowl layer pudding mixture with banana slices and chopped peanuts.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together the chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Put confectioners sugar in a bag or container with lid.
Pour in chocolate/cereal mix.
Shake together.
Store in covered container.
Do not refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Meat sauce:
Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain.
Add Ragu, tomatoes and tomato puree.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Then layer sauce, noodles and cheese until gone. Finish with cheese on top.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high 1 hour and low 2 to 3 hours.

title: frozen pecan pie
directions: In
large
bowl
beat
on high speed cream cheese, corn syrup and brown sugar until smooth.
On medium speed, mix milk and vanilla
into
mixture.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour in pie crust.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken with the chicken bouillon, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Don't use a lot of water.
Tear chicken into pieces when done and save the broth.
Grease with cooking spray a rectangular casserole dish.
With all of your ingredients at hand, with the broth warm, place 6 tortillas in broth to soak, but not too soggy or will tear.
Layer bottom of dish with tortillas, then spread 1/3 of the cream of mushroom and chicken soups onto tortillas.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the chicken onto soups, then 1/3 of the cheese onto chicken; repeat, beginning with the tortillas 2 more times.
Spread Ro-Tel tomatoes on top neatly, then sprinkle chili powder on for garnishing.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: strawberry short-cut cake
directions: Grease the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle marshmallows evenly on bottom of pan; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, thoroughly combine thawed strawberries with juice and strawberry dry jello mix; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients and beat well with an electric mixer (about 3 minutes).
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows in prepared pan.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center of cake.
Serve warm or cool with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: asparagus chestnut bake
directions: In buttered casserole, put layer of vegetables in order given; spoon and spread soup over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Melt butter over low heat.
Trim bread and cut each slice into 4 strips.
Dip bread strips in melted butter and lay over cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bread is golden brown.

title: double decker fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with tinfoil.
Place 1 cup peanut butter chips in medium size bowl; set aside.
Blend butter, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add peanut butter chips and set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix spinach, water chestnuts, soup mix, sour cream (you may use light sour cream, fat-free sour cream or yogurt instead), mayonnaise (you may use light or fat-free) and onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: mississippi mud sheet cake
directions: Combine sugar, 1/3 cup baking cocoa, oil, eggs, 1/2 cup milk, flour, 1 tablespoon vanilla and salt in a mixer bowl; beat until smooth. Stir in 1 cup pecans. Spoon into a greased and floured 10 x 14-inch cake pan. Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Sprinkle with marshmallows.

title: special pie crust
directions: Mix together into a ball.
Make 2 large crusts, 3 medium crusts or 4 small crusts.
This crust never fails.
It is always easy to make, easy to roll out, easy to handle and flaky when baked.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour to which soda and salt have been added.
Alternate with bananas and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Use 8x8 inch square or 9x5 inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar and flour with fruit in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, lemon juice and dot with margarine.
Add water, if desired.

title: pork in bourbon maple marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the pork, and pour into a nonmetal shallow dish. Add the pork tenderloin and allow to marinate overnight.

title: santa's thumbprints
directions: Mix all sugars and butter.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients together.
Add other ingredients to creamed mixture. Add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Shape into balls and put onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Make thumbprints.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Fill with jelly while still warm and top with pecans.

title: upside-down pie
directions: In an ovenproof skillet (10 to 11-inch), brown beef and cook celery, onion and green pepper in shortening until tender. Stir in soup and salt. Combine biscuit mix and milk and drop by spoonfuls over meat mixture. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Turn upside down on platter. Top with cheese.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon in wok.
Leave grease in wok and remove bacon.
Add dry seasonings.
Soft scramble egg.
Add bacon, ham, sherry and stock.
Next, add lettuce and onions and saute lightly.
Add rice on top.
Do not stir.
Cover for 1 minute.
Remove lid and stir. Serve.

title: country peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water.
When mixture starts to boil, add butter.
When it reaches 280° on candy thermometer, add peanuts and boil to 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla; mix well.
Put on two warm, buttered cookie sheets.
Crack into pieces when cool.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar with butter.
Sift salt, soda with flour and add it alternately with the buttermilk.
Melt the chocolate in hot water over low heat.
Add chocolate to the batter after the chocolate has cooled.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Make this in three 8-inch layers.

title: whiskey wieners
directions: Mix and boil with 1 pound beef wieners, cut in 1 inch pieces or use cocktail wieners.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Serve in heated chafing dish.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Heat tomato juice and beans. Add ground beef; bring to boil.
Add brown sugar.
Add salt and pepper plus chili powder
if needed.

title: dakota's favorite - thousand island taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef until
all is cooked and crumbly; add onion when it is about
half
done.
Drain
grease.
Add	taco seasoning mix according
to	package
directions.
Add
beans (undrained) and continue cooking until beans are hot.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle potato chips over top of mixture made from rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: greek butter twist cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Beat for 10 minutes until fluffy.
Add vanilla and cream.
Add eggs and beat 4 minutes.
Add baking powder.
Add enough flour slowly to make a soft, stiff dough.
Take a small amount of dough, roll into strips and shape into twists.
Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Brush each cookie with beaten egg yolk.
Bake in a 375° oven approximately 20 minutes until lightly brown.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: aunt macie ratchford's pound cake(heritage)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Divide milk.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking powder to 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining 1/2 teaspoon baking powder to flour and sift together.
Add flour alternately with remaining 1/2 cup milk, to the butter-sugar mixture.
Add baking powder-milk mixture after all dry ingredients have been blended.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Using a piece of thread, cut dough into 1/8-inch thick slices. Overlap slices on greased pizza pan.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Cream next 3 ingredients and spread onto warm crust. Garnish with sliced fruit (bananas, kiwi, blueberries, mandarin oranges, cherries).

title: blueberry apple jam with cinnamon
directions: Peel apple and grate into large saucepan.
Grate yellow zest from the lemon into pan and squeeze in the juice.
Add blueberries and sugar.
Lightly crush berries.
Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Skim any foam that rises to the surface while cooking.
Reduce heat and simmer until jam reaches the sheeting stage (220°), about 35 minutes.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix soup with reserved pea liquid and combine all remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in buttered dish.

title: apricot kuchen
directions: Mix the roll mix according to the directions on the box, but do not let it rise again after rolling it.
Use a large cookie sheet with sides and roll or press the dough out to fit it, making a small ridge around the edges.
Mix the sugar and flour together and add this to the cream.
Cook this until thick, stirring constantly.
Use a double boiler or else put the pan with the cream in a larger pan of water.
Spread 1/2 of the cream mixture on the dough.
Put fruit on top of this and bake at 350° until the edges are golden brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Cool to room temperature and spread the remaining cream on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
It is better if it is not refrigerated and it will keep for a day of so without refrigeration.

title: pork chops(microwave)
directions: Mix water and mushroom soup together.
Place pork chops in microwavable casserole pan and pour soup mixture over pork chops. Cover with lid.
Microwave on Medium or slow cook for 35 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet n' sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form into balls; fry.
Add grape jelly and chili sauce to meatballs and heat.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine strawberry juice and marshmallows in a double boiler. Heat until melted.
Cool.
Add cream cheese, salad dressing, pineapple and sliced strawberries.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
